Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.62,0:00:57.92,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这里是1959年勒芒24小时耐力赛的现场直播\NThis is live coverage of the 1959 24 Hours of Le Mans.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.92,0:00:59.38,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,比赛已经进行到了一半\NWe've reached the halfway point
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.38,0:01:01.84,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,到目前为止  我们目睹了由卡罗尔·谢尔比驾驶的\Nand so far witnessed Aston Martin number 5,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.84,0:01:03.51,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,阿斯顿马丁5号\Ndriven by Carroll Shelby,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.51,0:01:05.83,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,在过去的一小时里增加了大量行驶里程\Nmaking great gains in the last hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.93,0:01:07.43,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,如果他继续保持当前的速度\NIf he keeps this pace up,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.69,0:01:08.86,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,极速车王
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.43,0:01:09.41,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他就有可能赢得...\Nhe could have a chance at the...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.61,0:01:23.61,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,燃油
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.45,0:01:27.68,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他要进站了\NHe's coming in.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.16,0:01:30.03,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他要进站了  快点  行动起来\NHe's coming in. Let's go, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.03,0:01:31.91,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-拿轮胎  -快点  行动起来\N- Tires! - Let's go, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.91,0:01:34.29,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我知道你们累了  加把劲  速战速决\NI know you're tired, but come on, let's make this fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.29,0:01:35.77,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,动起来  动起来  快\NMove, move, move!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.92,0:01:39.57,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,它有点过热  但没什么大问题\NShe's running a little hot, but we're good.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.67,0:01:40.79,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,轮胎还有抓地力\NTires are still gripping.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.80,0:01:42.38,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-着火了  -油点着了\N- Fire! - The fuel! Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.38,0:01:44.16,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-谢尔比  你着火了  - 把那条毯子拿来\N- Shelby, it's you! - Grab that blanket!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.34,0:01:47.08,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,放开我  放开\NGet off me! Off!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.72,0:01:50.62,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你还好吗\NYou okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.47,0:01:54.58,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,给油箱加油啊\NFill the tank!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.48,0:01:58.42,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-谢尔比  你刚刚...  -我身上着火了吗\N- Shelby, you just... - Am I on fire?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.77,0:02:01.86,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我他妈身上着火了吗\NAm I on goddamn fire?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.86,0:02:03.57,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-你没着火  -那就赶快给油箱加油\N- No, you're not on fire. - Fill the damn tank!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.57,0:02:04.73,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-加油  -加油\N- Fill the tank. - Fill the tank.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.74,0:02:05.84,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,准备好\NGet it ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.95,0:02:09.07,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-我现在在什么位置  艾迪  -领先两圈\N- Where am I, Eddie? - Two laps up, my friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.07,0:02:10.06,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,车准备好了\NCar's yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.41,0:02:11.31,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,上吧\NGo get 'em.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.81,0:02:36.68,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,由卡罗尔·谢尔比驾驶的阿斯顿马丁5号\NAston Martin number 5, driven by Carroll Shelby,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.68,0:02:37.98,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,在比赛将要结束时\Nhas maintained his lead
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.98,0:02:40.31,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,保持了领先地位\Nas we're nearing the final minutes of the race.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.31,0:02:41.17,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,谢尔比\NShelby.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.69,0:02:43.26,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,方格旗已经出现了\NThe checkered flag is out.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.15,0:02:45.84,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,观众们翘首以盼\NThe crowd are on their feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.15,0:02:46.65,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,谢尔比\NShelby.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.65,0:02:47.94,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,赢得了冠军\Ntakes the title!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.95,0:02:49.74,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,一个美国人赢了勒芒耐力赛\NAn American wins Le Mans.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.74,0:02:50.64,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,谢尔比\NShelby.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.37,0:02:53.20,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,卡罗尔·谢尔比\NCarroll Shelby.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.20,0:02:53.93,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,什么\NWhat?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.45,0:02:56.70,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这事你不能再无视下去了\NThis is something you can't ignore anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.70,0:02:58.94,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我吃药啊  药片有用的\NOh, I take the pills. The pills work.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.75,0:03:03.00,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,过快的心率  比如每分钟130下\NAn elevated heart rate, say 130 BPM,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.00,0:03:05.46,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,即使持续时间很短\Nsustained even for a short period,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.46,0:03:07.21,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你也很有可能会心跳骤停\Nyou run a critical risk of cardiac arrest.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.21,0:03:09.59,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-那我就开一些短程比赛  -那样也没用\N- I'll race shorter format then. - That's not gonna work.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.59,0:03:12.43,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我可以开纳斯卡车赛  F1锦标赛\NWell, I could race NASCAR. Formula One.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.43,0:03:14.54,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你的心脏瓣膜撑不住了  谢尔比\NThe valve is shot, Shelby.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.01,0:03:16.22,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这件事很严重\NThis is as serious as it gets.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.22,0:03:18.96,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,在我看来  你今天能坐在这里就已经是万幸了\NIn my opinion, you're lucky to be sitting here today.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.52,0:03:22.21,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我确实觉得自己很幸运\NWell, I feel real lucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.44,0:03:24.97,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我觉得我是全世界最幸运的人\NLuckiest guy on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.08,0:03:44.27,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,在七千转时\NThere's a point.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.21,0:03:49.12,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,有一个临界点  一切都变得虚无\N7,000 RPM where everything fades.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.02,0:04:00.71,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,车失去了重量\NThe machine becomes weightless.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.10,0:04:02.54,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,直接消失了\NJust disappears.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.77,0:04:06.47,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,当心点  伙计\NWatch it, buddy!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.03,0:04:13.85,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,只留下一具躯壳\NAnd all that's left is a body
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.91,0:04:15.89,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,在时空中穿梭\Nmoving through space and time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.08,0:04:23.77,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,七千转\N7,000 RPM.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.50,0:04:26.99,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,就是那个临界点\NThat's where you meet it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.72,0:04:32.16,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,它会向你提出一个问题\NIt asks you a question.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.43,0:04:35.24,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,一个终极的问题\NThe only question that matters.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.43,0:04:39.33,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,"你究竟是谁"\N"Who are you?"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.73,0:04:48.86,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,现在驾驶法拉利的是冯·特里普斯\NNow, it's von Trips in the Ferrari,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.86,0:04:50.11,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他来到了下坡急弯\Ncoming into the corkscrew.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.11,0:04:52.78,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我给你打了三次电话  你一次都没回我\NHey, I called you three times, and you never answer the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.19,0:04:52.30,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他在延迟刹车\NHe's braking late.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.74,0:04:56.07,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他创造了新的圈速纪录\NOh! He sets a new lap record!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.36,0:04:55.49,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,每个电话我都会接\NI answer the phone every time it rings.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.49,0:04:56.45,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,不  先生  你没接\NNo, sir, you do not.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.45,0:04:57.49,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我接了\NYes, I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.49,0:04:58.66,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,不  你没接\NNo, you don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.66,0:05:00.77,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,一个月前  这辆车还好好的\NA month ago, this car was fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.45,0:05:03.54,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,现在都没法发动了\NNow, it won't even start.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.54,0:05:06.48,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,每次一发动  就砰砰作响\NAnd when it does, it's, "Boom, boom, boom!"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.71,0:05:08.50,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我把这车开出车道\NWhen I pull out of the driveway,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.50,0:05:10.45,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,路旁的狗都要吓出心脏病\Nthe dog has a heart attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.13,0:05:13.53,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我只希望你能把这车修好\NAll I'm asking is for you to make it like it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.18,0:05:16.89,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你把进气阀和火花塞憋住了\NYeah, you've coked up the inlet valves and the plugs.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.89,0:05:18.14,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,车没问题\NNothing wrong with the car,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.14,0:05:19.26,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,有问题的是开车方式\Njust the way it's being driven.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.26,0:05:20.43,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,开车方式\NThe way it's being driven?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.43,0:05:21.51,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,燃料太多  火星不够\NToo much fuel, not enough spark.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.52,0:05:22.77,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,所以它才会打不着火\NThat's what's making her misfire.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.77,0:05:24.42,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你想用人话跟我解释一遍吗\NYou wanna run that by me in English?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.69,0:05:27.84,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,好吧  先生\NAll right, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.11,0:05:30.22,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你看啊\NSo...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.07,0:05:34.44,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,那边那辆车  是辆跑车\Nthat there, that is a sport car.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.45,0:05:36.65,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你必须用开跑车的方法来开她\NYou have to drive her like a sport car.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.66,0:05:38.45,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,如果你像个学校老师一样来开她\NIf you drive her like a school teacher,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.45,0:05:39.91,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,它就会堵塞  知道吗\Nshe'll clog up. All right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.91,0:05:43.27,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,等五千转的时候再换挡  别两千转就换\NTry changing up at 5,000 RPM, not two.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.41,0:05:47.57,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,开车的时候认真点  干脆利落\NDrive like you mean it. Hard and tight.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.83,0:05:48.98,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,它就会顺畅无阻了\NShe'll run clean.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.29,0:05:52.65,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你是在跟我说我不知道怎么开自己的车吗\NAre you telling me I don't know how to drive my own car?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.05,0:05:54.91,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,不是\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.59,0:05:57.18,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,但如果你问我的话  你确实驾驭不了这车\NBut if you ask me, this isn't your car.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.18,0:06:01.12,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,普利茅斯或者斯图贝克这种车更适合你\NYour car's more a Plymouth or a Studebaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.72,0:06:04.46,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你是对我有什么意见吗  伙计\NYou and me have a problem, buddy?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.60,0:06:06.98,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我没有意见  我曾经有辆名爵\NI don't have a problem. I had an MG.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.98,0:06:08.50,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我的车开着就挺好\NMine ran just fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.52,0:06:10.40,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,去你的  你这个狗屁英国佬\NScrew you, you limey prick.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.40,0:06:11.40,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我要退款\NI want my money back.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.40,0:06:14.13,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,文明一点  退给你就是了\NOh, behave. I'd give it to ya.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.24,0:06:16.03,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,但你上个月的保养费还没给呢\NBut you haven't paid for last month's service yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.03,0:06:18.72,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,在这个国家  顾客就是上帝\NThis country, the customer's always right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.03,0:06:19.78,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你没听说过吗\NYou ever hear that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.78,0:06:21.89,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,听过  听过\NYeah. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.99,0:06:23.89,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,完全就是屁话\NUtter nonsense.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.99,0:06:26.50,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,记好了  我把定时链调快了\NNow remember, I advanced the timing,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.50,0:06:28.90,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,所以刚开始车会有点抖\Nso a smidge twitchy in first.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.42,0:06:32.78,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,把转速提上去  就这样  转速提上去\NGet the revs up. Good lad. Revs up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.17,0:06:35.20,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,再见\NTa-ra.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.97,0:06:39.83,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,又是一个满意而归的顾客吗\NAnother satisfied customer?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.76,0:06:44.00,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,何事需要效劳  小姐\NCan I help you, miss?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.27,0:06:48.38,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,刚刚那辆不是名爵的MGA 1500吗\NWasn't that an MGA 1500?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.85,0:06:52.71,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你很懂车嘛\NYou know your cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.73,0:06:54.05,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我很喜欢车\NWell, I like them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.48,0:06:56.13,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我喜欢发动机的轰鸣声\NI love the sound they make.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.44,0:06:58.18,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,那声音直接穿过你的身体\NThe way it goes right through you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.45,0:06:59.55,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,没错\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.41,0:07:01.85,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,那种振动\NThat vibration.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.99,0:07:07.75,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我的车是那辆镶木板的\NMine's the wood-paneled
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.75,0:07:09.65,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,福特乡绅\NCountry Squire...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.00,0:07:11.57,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,就停在街对面\Nacross the street.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.67,0:07:14.96,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,一辆改装的大马力车\NA real hot rod.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.96,0:07:15.99,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,是吗\NOh, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.38,0:07:17.95,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-开得快吗  -非常快\N- Is it fast? - Very.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.01,0:07:21.16,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,等等  你是哪种女孩\NWait a second. What type of girl are ya?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.51,0:07:24.12,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我这种女孩喜欢闻汽油味\NType of girl who likes the smell of wet gasoline.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.26,0:07:25.22,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,和烧过的橡胶味\NBurnt rubber.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.22,0:07:28.54,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,那你有点离经叛道  不是吗\NOh, what, are you some kind of a deviant, are ya?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.06,0:07:30.79,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,还不是因为我嫁给了你\NWell, only since I married you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.11,0:07:40.28,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,加尔  怎么回事\NHey, Gar, what's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.28,0:07:41.35,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,出事了\NSomething's up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.99,0:07:43.66,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你好  李\NHi, Lee.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.66,0:07:46.23,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,听着  银行这事他没你确定\NListen, he isn't as sure as you are about the banks.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.29,0:07:50.31,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我也不确定这事...\NI'm not as sure about this...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.79,0:07:52.48,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,进展如何\NHow's this going out?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.34,0:07:57.95,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-唐  怎么回事  -我不知道\N- Don, what's going on? - I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.63,0:08:00.88,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,福特先生  欢迎来到车间\NMr. Ford, welcome to the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.88,0:08:02.05,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,下午好  福特先生\NGood afternoon, Mr. Ford.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.05,0:08:03.33,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,幸会  先生\NNice to see you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.39,0:08:10.42,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,停工  毕比先生\NShut it down, Mr. Beebe.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.82,0:08:17.76,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,约翰\NJohn!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.32,0:08:23.39,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,全部停下\NAll stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.00,0:08:36.11,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,听见那声音了吗\NHear that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.17,0:08:43.28,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,那就是福特汽车公司\NThat's the sound of the Ford Motor Company...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.76,0:08:45.62,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,要倒闭的声音\Nout of business.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.31,0:08:56.80,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,1899年  我的祖父亨利·福特\NIn 1899, my grandfather, Henry, by God, Ford...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.15,0:09:00.40,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,从爱迪生照明公司走回家\Nwas walking home from Edison Illumination
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.40,0:09:02.68,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他那时刚上完两轮班\Nafter working a double shift.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.74,0:09:04.51,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他左思右想\NHe was ruminating.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.82,0:09:07.74,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,那个清晨  他产生了一个想法\NThat morning, he had himself an idea
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.74,0:09:09.64,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,那个想法改变了世界\Nthat changed the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.29,0:09:12.25,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,65年过去了\NSixty-five years
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.25,0:09:15.62,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,在生产了四千七百万辆车之后\Nand 47 million automobiles later,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.62,0:09:18.03,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他将留下什么\Nwhat shall be his legacy?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.88,0:09:23.74,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,雪佛兰羚羊排出的尾气\NGetting it in the tail pipe from a Chevy Impala.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.90,0:09:23.78,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,通用汽车旗下雪佛兰的畅销车型
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.10,0:09:29.96,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我希望你们做如下事项\NHere's what I want you to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.10,0:09:31.96,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,走回家\NWalk home.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.23,0:09:39.17,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你们在走的时候  我希望你们能好好思索\NWhile you're walking, I want you to ruminate.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.40,0:09:42.55,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,谁能带着想法走进我的办公室\NMan comes to my office with an idea,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.67,0:09:45.22,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,谁就能保住工作\Nthat man keeps his job.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.03,0:09:49.14,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,其他的二流失败者...\NRest of you second-best losers...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.70,0:09:51.10,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,就待在家里吧\Nstay home.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.16,0:09:53.27,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你不属于福特公司\NYou don't belong at Ford.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.01,0:10:04.28,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,谢尔比\NShelby!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.63,0:10:10.20,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我看见你了  该起床了  伙计\NI see you. Up and at 'em, buddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.72,0:10:16.84,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-走开  -快点  你可以的\N- Go away. - Come on. You can do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.98,0:10:19.17,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,快起床吧  宝贝\NCome on, baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.35,0:10:21.76,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,八点半了  该出发了\N8:30 a.m., time to roll.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.77,0:10:22.88,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,快来\NLet's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.65,0:10:25.57,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-快来快来  -滚开\N- Let's go. Let's go, go, go. - Go away.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.57,0:10:27.93,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,已经八点半了  宝贝  该出发了\NIt's 8:30 a.m., baby. Time to roll.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.24,0:10:30.31,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,走吧\NCome on.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.66,0:10:32.58,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你好啊  菲尔\NHey, Phil.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.58,0:10:33.60,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你好啊  鲍勃\NHey, Bob.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.04,0:10:34.98,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,谢尔比在吗\NIs Shelby here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.54,0:10:36.98,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,很难说\Nit's touch and go.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.84,0:10:45.17,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,谢尔比  你起得可真早\NShelby, you're up bright and early.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.17,0:10:48.45,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,早起的鸟儿有虫吃嘛  老爹\NWell, early bird gets the worm, Pops.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.85,0:10:54.18,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,好吧  你担心谁\NAll right, who you worried about?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.18,0:10:57.18,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,瑞德·法里斯和比尔·拉什顿\NWell, you got Red Faris and Bill Rushton.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.18,0:10:58.77,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他们都开327发动机的\NThey're all in 327s.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.77,0:11:00.39,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,科尔维特  那邦杜兰特呢\NCorvettes. What about Bondurant?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.40,0:11:02.19,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,邦杜兰特吗  他还在给...\NBondurant? Well, he's still driving...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.19,0:11:04.30,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-谢尔比先生  能给我签个名吗  -沃什伯恩开车\N- Mr. Shelby, can I get an autograph? - for Washburn.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.11,0:11:06.80,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,614号\NNumber 614.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.61,0:11:09.20,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-太感谢了  -好了  放轻松\N- Thank you so much. - All right, just relax. All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.20,0:11:11.18,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,科尔维特那些车都不足挂齿\NWe're gonna eat those Vettes for breakfast.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.20,0:11:12.68,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我们更轻  更快\NWe're lighter, we're faster,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.78,0:11:14.64,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,如果这些都没用的话  我们更野\Nand that don't work, we're nastier.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.79,0:11:17.12,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,各位爸爸们  在比赛开始之前\NHey, Dad, before the race starts,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.12,0:11:19.16,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,带着你们的儿子来柳泉赛道看看吧...\Ntake your son over to the Willow Springs...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.16,0:11:22.03,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,菲尔  今天对我们手下留点情  老兄\NHey, Phil. Hey, take it easy on us today, bud.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.46,0:11:27.36,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,有什么问题吗\NYou all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.38,0:11:30.68,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,美国赛车俱乐部标准第2b节第15.4条\NParagraph 15.4, section 2b of the SCCA standard
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.68,0:11:32.97,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,规定了所有AF级赛车的后备箱容量\Ndictates all AF class cars must have
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.97,0:11:36.92,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,尺寸至少要长20英寸  宽12英寸  高6英寸\Nminimum trunk space of 20 inches by 12 inches by 6 inches.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.22,0:11:38.88,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你这车连后备箱都合不上\NYour trunk doesn't close.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.89,0:11:40.98,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-因此这辆车不符合标准  -等等  什么\N- Ergo car fails standard. - Wait, wait, wait. What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.98,0:11:43.16,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,因此这辆车没有资格\NErgo car is disqualified from
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.17,0:11:44.77,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-参加A级比赛  -不不不  听着\N- said Class A competition. - No, no, no. Look, look, look.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.77,0:11:46.40,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,让我问你个问题好吗\NCan I ask you a question, all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.40,0:11:49.24,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,当你还是个小男孩的时候  你有没有想过\NWhen you were a little boy, did you think,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.24,0:11:50.24,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,"等我长大了\N"When I grow up,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.68,0:11:53.61,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我想去传说中的柳泉赛道\NI want to go to the fabled Willow Springs Raceway,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.62,0:11:54.21,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,然后我想执行\Nand I want to enforce
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.21,0:11:56.41,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,美国赛车俱乐部标准第2b节第15.4条中\Nparagraph 15.4, section 2b
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.41,0:11:59.04,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,关于后备箱容量的规定"\Nof the SCCA regulations on luggage capacity"?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.04,0:12:00.79,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-好了  就这样  -你想过吗\N- All right, that's it. - Did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.79,0:12:04.03,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我要取消你和你的队伍的参赛资格\NI'm ruling you and your team disqualified from this race.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.17,0:12:07.59,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这该不会是兰斯·瑞文特罗吧\NWell, if it isn't Lance Reventlow.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.59,0:12:09.76,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-谢尔比  -你最近怎么样  兰斯\N- Shelby. - How you doing, Lance?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.76,0:12:10.72,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-老爹  -你好啊  兰斯\N- Pops. - Hey, Lance.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.72,0:12:12.34,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,请允许我向你们介绍迪特·沃斯\NAllow me to introduce Dieter Voss.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.34,0:12:13.43,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他在杰克逊维尔运营着布鲁莫斯保时捷车队\NRuns Brumos Porsche out of Jacksonville.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.43,0:12:15.47,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,久仰沃斯先生大名\NOh, I know all about Mr. Voss.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.47,0:12:17.75,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你可是用那辆阿巴斯在赛季取得了辉煌战绩啊  先生\NYou're having a hell of a season with that Abarth, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.89,0:12:20.27,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-你那辆福特眼镜蛇也是战果累累  -多谢夸奖\N- Seeing results for your Cobra, too. - Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.27,0:12:21.77,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你手下那个叫迈尔斯的挺不错\NYour guy Miles is impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.77,0:12:23.60,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-你还在关注迈尔斯  -没错\N- Oh, you following Miles? - Oh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.60,0:12:26.36,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他在1961年赢得了美国汽车俱乐部竞速赛冠军\NWell, he was a USAC road racing champ in '61.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.36,0:12:27.82,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他赢下了派克峰登山赛\NHe won the Pikes Peak Hill Climb.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.82,0:12:30.74,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他连续三年赢得美国赛车俱乐部C级冠军赛\NHe was SCCA C-class champion three years in a row
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.74,0:12:32.82,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,开的还是那辆他自己造的破名爵\Nin this piece-of-shit MG he built himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.82,0:12:34.70,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我们听说他很难搞\NWe heard he's, difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.70,0:12:36.78,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,什么  肯吗  不不  肯就是一只小狗狗\NWhat, Ken? No, no. Ken's a puppy dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.78,0:12:38.95,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,兰斯  告诉他事实  你跟肯比赛过\NHey, Lance, tell the man. You've raced against Ken.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.95,0:12:41.31,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,谈不上比赛吧  几乎都是我落后\NOh, I've driven more behind him than against him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.04,0:12:44.54,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,布鲁莫斯正在找车手\NWell, Brumos is looking for a driver
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.54,0:12:46.71,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,来驾驶我们在赛百灵耐力赛中的2号车\Nfor our number two car at Sebring.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.71,0:12:48.09,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-是吗  -这怎么可能\N- Is that right? - How is that even possible?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.09,0:12:50.09,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你觉得你手下的迈尔斯可以吗\NThink your guy Miles can make the grade?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.09,0:12:51.99,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-肯这个人...  -他有没有这么做  伙计\N- Oh, well, Ken... - Is he, mate? Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.26,0:12:54.72,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,吉姆  他有没有把他所有的行李\NJim! Is he putting his bloody carryal
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.72,0:12:56.18,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-都放进你的后备箱  -什么\N- in your trunk? - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.18,0:12:57.43,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这是可自由裁量的违规\NDiscretionary infraction.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.43,0:12:58.96,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,各位  失陪一会\NGentlemen, excuse me a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.85,0:13:02.67,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,说实话  肯就是为了赛百灵耐力赛而生的\NTo be honest, Ken was born for Sebring.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.52,0:13:06.15,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这里面没有哪句话规定了后备箱尺寸\NNothing in there about my trunk
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.15,0:13:08.98,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,也没规定你那可爱的小行李箱的尺寸\Nand your lovely little portmanteau.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.98,0:13:11.76,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你拿的是1962年那版的老标准\NYou're holding the '62 edition of the SCCA.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.32,0:13:16.06,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你可以把这张该死的贴纸\NAnd you can stick this bloody sticker
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.62,0:13:18.66,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,贴在见不得光的地方\Nwhere the sun don't shine.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.66,0:13:19.91,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,比尔  有什么问题吗  比尔\NHey, Bill. What seems to be the problem, Bill?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.91,0:13:22.62,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,问题就是这位比尔是个混蛋\NThe problem is that Bill here is an arsehole.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.62,0:13:24.96,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-他不是真心的  -他就是真心的\N- No, he doesn't mean that. - Oh, yes, he does. Yes, he does.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.96,0:13:28.17,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,不  他真的觉得比尔就是个混蛋\NNo, he really does think that Bill is an arsehole.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.17,0:13:30.46,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-我只是在尽我的职责  -别急  比尔\N- I'm just doing my job here. - Hang on. Bill, Bill, Bill.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.46,0:13:32.67,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,依我的经验看  肯定有...听我说\NIn my experience, there is... Listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.67,0:13:34.63,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,一般这种事  肯定有折中办法\NSomething like this, there's always a middle ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.63,0:13:36.72,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-好吗  肯是有点过分  -我只是在尽我的职责\N- All right? Now, Ken's outta line. - And I'm just doing my job.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.72,0:13:37.68,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这我也理解\NI understand you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.68,0:13:38.89,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你也知道他在比赛日的表现\NYou know how he gets on a race day.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.89,0:13:39.97,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你清楚的  不是吗\NYou know that. All right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.97,0:13:41.79,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你也没必要因为一个后备箱就取消我们的比赛资格\NBut you're not gonna DQ us over a trunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.69,0:13:50.22,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-什么  -你看见那家伙了吗\N- What? - You see that guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.98,0:13:51.97,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,兴致勃勃的\NGot his tail up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.45,0:14:00.77,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,高兴了吗  比尔\NHappy, Bill?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.83,0:14:05.16,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,比尔  我来处理吧  我来跟他谈谈\NBill, I'll handle it. I'll talk to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.16,0:14:07.29,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我来跟他谈谈  你就好好去享受今天吧\NI'll talk to him. You just go and have a great day.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.29,0:14:09.23,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,各位  饿了吗\NHey, folks, feeling hungry?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.50,0:14:11.19,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,那不妨去零食吧转转...\NHead on over to the snack bar...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.71,0:14:12.95,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,该死\NShit.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.13,0:14:14.03,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,斗牛犬\NBulldog.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.97,0:14:17.59,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你知道刚刚我在跟谁谈话吗\NYou know who that was I was just talking to?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.59,0:14:18.37,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,比尔\NBill.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.72,0:14:19.91,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-在那之前  -不知道\N- Before that. - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.43,0:14:21.96,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,是迪特·沃斯\NIt was Dieter Voss.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.06,0:14:22.96,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他是哪位\NWho's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.35,0:14:26.21,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他运营着保时捷车队  肯\NHe runs Porsche, Ken.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.31,0:14:28.69,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,是个德国的小汽车公司  你或许有所耳闻\NIt's a little German car company. Maybe you heard of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.69,0:14:29.40,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,好吧\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.40,0:14:31.02,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他想让你代表他们参加赛百灵耐力赛\NHe wanted you to drive at Sebring.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.02,0:14:32.55,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,但他听说你很难搞\NBut he'd heard you were difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.07,0:14:42.98,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我还以为我们对德国人看法相同\NI thought we felt the same way about, Germans.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.66,0:14:49.23,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你喜欢输吗  肯\NDo you like losing, Ken?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.42,0:14:52.53,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你说什么\NExcuse me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.54,0:14:53.61,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你听见了\NOh, you heard me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.80,0:14:55.86,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我不会输\NI don't lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.67,0:14:59.95,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,没有赞助商  你就没有车  肯\NWithout sponsors, you get no car, Ken.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.18,0:15:02.05,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,据我所知  所有的职业赛车手\NAnd last I checked, the professionals
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.05,0:15:03.68,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-都有辆车  -谢尔\N- all have a car. - Shel!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.68,0:15:05.97,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,没车你根本赢不了美国赛车俱乐部的比赛\NYou cannot win the SCCA without one.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.97,0:15:07.89,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,如果你赢不了 那就是输了\NIf you're not winning, you are losing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.89,0:15:10.35,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,别逼我用这玩意给你的脑门来一下\NDon't make me lamp this at your head.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.35,0:15:11.65,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你大老远地把你儿子带来这里\NDid you bring your son all the way out here
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.65,0:15:12.86,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,是为了让他来看你被取消比赛资格\Nto watch you get disqualified
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.86,0:15:14.72,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,还是为了让他见识你这副混蛋模样\Nor just act like a jackass?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.78,0:15:19.76,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,牛逼\NDamn!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.20,0:15:24.52,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你身体力行地回答了这个问题\NWell, that answers that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.05,0:15:44.33,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,彼得\NPeter...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.81,0:15:55.47,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,有什么事吗  先生们\NMay I help you, gentlemen?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.40,0:15:57.28,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,肯·迈尔斯有限公司\N外国车专家\N大修\N发动机调校
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.61,0:15:57.51,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,肯·迈尔斯在吗\NYes, is Ken Miles here?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.90,0:15:58.76,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,不在\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.90,0:16:00.19,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我们想跟迈尔斯先生谈谈\NWe need to speak to Mr. Miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.20,0:16:01.24,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我是他妻子\NI'm his wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.24,0:16:05.37,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,欢迎来到1963年柳泉赛道竞速赛\NWelcome to the 1963 Willow Springs 100.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.37,0:16:08.56,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,十二辆车将在四十圈的比赛中进行角逐\NTwelve cars will be competing in this 40-lap race.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.20,0:16:12.19,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,肯  你的挡风玻璃怎么了\NHey, Ken, what happened to your shield?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.21,0:16:14.61,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这是新设计\NNew design.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.84,0:16:17.74,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,看来比赛即将开始\NWell, it looks like we're about to begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.84,0:16:20.03,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,赛车已经完成了暖胎圈\NThe cars have completed their warm-up lap.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.51,0:16:21.83,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,绿旗已出\NThe green flag is out...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.84,0:16:24.95,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,赛车正在接近起点线\Nand they're approaching the starting line.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.26,0:16:26.75,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,来吧\NHere we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.89,0:16:31.13,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,该死的\NOh, bloody hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.27,0:16:36.01,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,肯·迈尔斯目前处于落后位置\NKen Miles has fallen behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.31,0:16:38.38,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,学学怎么开车吧  蠢货\NLearn to drive, you pillock!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.36,0:16:45.89,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,谢尔比  你怀念这些吗\NSo, Shelby, do you miss it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.37,0:16:49.39,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你好啊  萨姆\NHey, Sam.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.70,0:16:54.15,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,勒芒24小时耐力赛冠军得主  忽然之间就退役了\NGuy wins the 24-hour Le Mans, suddenly retires,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.37,0:16:55.73,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,开始卖车了\Nstarts selling cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.21,0:16:58.38,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这说不通\NIt just don't make sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.38,0:17:00.78,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,当然  除非谣言是真的\NWell, unless the rumors are true, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.13,0:17:03.03,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,什么谣言  萨姆\NOh, what rumors would those be, Sam?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.30,0:17:06.91,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,卡罗尔·谢尔比不开车了  因为他没那个胆量了\NThat Carroll Shelby quit driving 'cause he lost his nerve.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.52,0:17:15.42,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,下个弯我要延迟制动超你车  鲍勃\NI'm gonna out-brake you on the next turn, Bob.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.70,0:17:29.02,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,想得美  鲍勃\NNice try, Bob.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.05,0:17:48.51,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,肯·迈尔斯完成了一次漂亮的超车\NNice move from Ken Miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.51,0:17:49.72,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,还剩22圈\NTwenty-two laps remaining,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.72,0:17:51.83,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,目前领先的是菲尔·希尔和丹·格尼\Nwith Phil Hill and Dan Gurney in the lead.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.70,0:18:17.41,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,今天的柳泉赛道真是精彩纷呈\NIt's been an incredible day here at Willow Springs,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.42,0:18:19.61,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我们也目睹了一些激动人心的车技\Nand we've seen some exciting driving.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.75,0:18:23.09,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,四十圈的比赛还剩下最后一圈\NWith just one lap remaining in this 40-lap race,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.09,0:18:25.09,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,马上就要进入最后阶段了\Nwe're coming to the final stretch.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.09,0:18:28.20,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,丹·格尼在比赛的大部分时间里都处于领先...\NDan Gurney has been leading the pack for most of the...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.35,0:18:32.54,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,18号  瑞德·法瑞斯  脱离赛道\NNumber 18, Red Faris, is off the track.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.93,0:18:34.72,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,所以目前丹·格尼领先\NThat leaves Dan Gurney for the lead
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.72,0:18:37.00,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,后面紧跟着经验丰富的肯·迈尔斯\Nfollowed by journeyman Ken Miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.52,0:18:40.92,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,轮到你了  丹\NNow for you, Dan.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.07,0:18:48.14,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他们即将经过最后一个弯道\NAnd they're coming around the last turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.20,0:18:49.74,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,格尼依旧领先\NGurney is still in the lead
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.74,0:18:51.56,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,肯·迈尔斯紧随其后\Nwith Ken Miles hot on his heels.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.17,0:19:00.79,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,迈尔斯在找缺口超车\NMiles is looking for an opening.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.79,0:19:01.73,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,等等\NNot yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.34,0:19:03.40,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,快呀\NCome on.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.71,0:19:06.80,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,格尼能在最后的直道挡住他吗\NCan Gurney hold him off in the final straight?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.80,0:19:07.74,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,再等等\NNot yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.51,0:19:12.04,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,格尼在挡他\NGurney is blocking him out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.22,0:19:13.04,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,就现在\NNow.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.68,0:19:18.38,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,迈尔斯冲上了路肩\NMiles goes for the shoulder.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.64,0:19:19.92,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这一下很漂亮  肯\NNice move, Ken.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.48,0:19:25.61,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,现在两辆车并驾齐驱了\NThey're wheel to wheel.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.61,0:19:26.68,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,加把劲啊\NCome on.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.94,0:19:29.72,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,雪佛兰科尔维特和福特眼镜蛇在终点前的对决\NIt's Corvette versus Cobra for the finish.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.66,0:19:38.98,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,肯·迈尔斯完成了不可思议的终场逆袭\NAn incredible finish for Ken Miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.46,0:19:41.02,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,让人意想不到\NDidn't see that one coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.42,0:19:45.38,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他虽然难搞  但车技不错\NHe's difficult but good.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.38,0:19:47.96,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,大家请为这场精彩比赛中的每一位选手送上掌声\NLet's give everyone a hand for one heck of a race.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.96,0:19:50.70,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这我可得喝杯好茶\NThat calls for a nice cup of tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.88,0:19:52.49,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我去烧水\NI'll put the kettle on.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.72,0:19:53.79,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,上来\NHop in.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.06,0:19:59.98,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,♪ 我 ♪\N♪ I'm ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.98,0:20:01.89,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,♪ 快快乐乐 ♪\N♪ H-a-p-p-y ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.90,0:20:03.98,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,♪ 我快快乐乐 ♪\N♪ I'm h-a-p-p-y ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.98,0:20:08.34,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,♪ 我确定一定以及肯定自己快快乐乐 ♪\N♪ I know I am, I'm sure I am I'm h-a-p-p-y ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.07,0:20:11.64,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,老爹  给这玩意裱个框\NPops, frame this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.75,0:20:27.95,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我们赢了\NWe did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.42,0:20:31.37,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,出了什么事\NWhat's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.64,0:20:34.91,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,国税局的人来了\NThe IRS came.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.85,0:20:37.25,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他们封了修车店\NThey've padlocked the garage.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.77,0:20:44.25,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,好好睡吧  彼得\NAll right, Petey.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.33,0:20:58.81,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,几年前...\NA couple of years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.95,0:21:01.48,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你说过我们有储蓄\Nyou said we'd a nest egg.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.04,0:21:02.98,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,没错\NCorrect.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.75,0:21:06.04,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,几年前你就说过\NA couple of years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.04,0:21:07.24,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,没错\NCorrect.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.38,0:21:14.78,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,所以我得说清楚  我们破产了\NSo just to be clear, we are buggered.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.09,0:21:16.41,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,确实\NAbsolutely.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.31,0:21:24.75,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,什么都没了吗\NAs in totally?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.48,0:21:30.51,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,可以说是分文不剩  身无长物\NAs in, not a bean, or a pot in which to piss.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.65,0:21:33.61,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,备件  存货  都没了\NSpares, stock, all gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.61,0:21:36.14,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,工具  我的工具还都被锁在了里面\NTools. My tools are locked up in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.49,0:21:39.43,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我会想办法解决的\NI'll figure something out.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.70,0:21:42.66,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,福特公司
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.12,0:21:42.87,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,1945年\NIn 1945...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.87,0:21:44.56,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我们的士兵们打完仗回了家\Nour soldiers came home.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.54,0:21:47.44,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他们回家做的第一件事是什么呢\NWhat was the first thing that they did?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.46,0:21:50.65,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,做爱\NThey had sex.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.34,0:21:53.87,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,十七年后\NSeventeen years later,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.88,0:21:55.58,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,当年出生的那些婴儿都长大了\Nthose babies, they've grown.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.76,0:21:57.12,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他们找了工作\NAnd they've got jobs.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.68,0:21:59.25,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,也考了驾照\NThey've got licenses.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.39,0:22:03.18,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,但他们不想跟他们的父母一样\NBut they do not wanna drive the same dull 50s cars
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.18,0:22:04.71,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,开着五十年代的老旧车型\Nthat their parents drove.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.23,0:22:07.90,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,如今的孩子  想让自己有魅力\NYou see, kids today, they want glamour.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.90,0:22:10.19,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,想让自己有性吸引力\NThey want sex appeal.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.19,0:22:11.80,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,想追求更快的速度\NThey want to go fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.48,0:22:13.72,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,先生们\NGentlemen...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.86,0:22:16.26,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,福特汽车公司是时候开始\Nit's time for the Ford Motor Company
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.45,0:22:17.72,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,参赛了\Nto go racing.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.87,0:22:21.31,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我们已经在参赛了  艾亚科卡\NWe're already in racing, Iacocca.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.87,0:22:23.02,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,纳斯卡车赛吗\NNASCAR?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.16,0:22:25.40,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这只是地区性的  先生\NIt's... it's regional, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.91,0:22:28.92,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,如果你去看电影  或者翻开一本杂志\NIf you go to the movies, you open up a magazine,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.92,0:22:31.42,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你不会看到来自温斯顿-塞勒姆的好男孩组合\Nyou don't see good ol' boys from Winston-Salem.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.42,0:22:32.53,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你看见的都是...\NYou see...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.84,0:22:35.16,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,索菲娅·罗兰\NSophia Loren...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.42,0:22:37.74,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,莫尼卡·维蒂\NMonica Vitti.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.68,0:22:43.92,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,007可不会开福特出任务  先生\NJames Bond does not drive a Ford, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.35,0:22:46.63,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,那是因为他是个败类\NThat's because he's a degenerate.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.69,0:22:51.71,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,没错吧\NSee?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.77,0:22:53.63,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,天呐  我倒想做个败类\NGod, I'd like to be a degenerate.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.78,0:22:55.73,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,给我一点时间  先生\Njust give me one second here, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.74,0:22:56.84,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这是你展示的一部分吗\NIs this part of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.49,0:22:59.61,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这有什么意义吗  艾亚科卡\NIs this going anywhere, Iacocca?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.61,0:23:00.57,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,等等  先生\NJust a second, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.57,0:23:01.95,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,好了  好了  可以了\NAll right, all right, that's enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.95,0:23:02.83,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,先生  麻烦您再等我...\NSir, if you just bear with me...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.83,0:23:04.35,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,关掉  开灯\NTurn it off. Lights.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.58,0:23:11.46,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,李  在过去的三年里\NLee, in the last three years,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.46,0:23:13.86,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,在你和你的营销团队的带领下\Nyou and your marketing team...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.30,0:23:18.99,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,公司经历了美国史上最严重的销量暴跌\Nhave presided over the worst sales slump in US history.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.14,0:23:23.75,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,福特先生到底为什么要听你的\NWhy exactly should Mr. Ford listen to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.98,0:23:28.83,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,因为一直以来我们都想错了\NBecause we've been thinking wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.19,0:23:33.34,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,法拉利\NFerrari.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.32,0:23:37.05,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,在最近五次勒芒赛中  法拉利赢了四次\NNow, they have won four out of the last five Le Mans.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.86,0:23:40.60,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我们得像法拉利一样思考\NWe need to think like Ferrari.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.03,0:23:42.91,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,法拉利一年造的车\NFerrari makes fewer cars
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.91,0:23:45.27,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,还没有我们一天造的多\Nin a year than we make in a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.08,0:23:48.37,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我们在厕纸上花的钱\NWe spend more on toilet paper
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.37,0:23:50.86,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,都比他们在生产上的全部投入要高\Nthan they do on their entire output.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.50,0:23:53.63,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你还想让我们像他们一样思考\NYou want us to think like them?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.63,0:23:55.79,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,恩佐·法拉利会名留青史\NEnzo Ferrari will go down in history
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.80,0:23:58.24,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,被称为史上最伟大的汽车制造者\Nas the greatest car manufacturer of all time.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.59,0:24:00.37,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,为什么\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.43,0:24:04.83,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,是因为他造的车最多吗\NIs it because he built the most cars?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.63,0:24:07.39,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,不\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.47,0:24:10.73,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,而是因为他的车所蕴含的意义\NIt's because of what his cars mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.93,0:24:12.74,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,胜利\NVictory.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.45,0:24:15.14,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,法拉利在勒芒赛上取胜了\NFerrari wins at Le Mans.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.14,0:24:18.85,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,人们...他们想要分享这种胜利\NPeople, they, they want some of that victory.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.88,0:24:24.33,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,如果福特的标志意味着胜利呢\NWhat if the Ford badge meant victory?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.65,0:24:25.71,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,而且这种意味被重要的人群认可\NAnd meant it where it counts,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.71,0:24:28.41,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,也就是那群史上第一批兜里有钱的\Nwith the first group of 17-year-olds in history
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.42,0:24:29.71,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,十七岁青少年\Nwith money in their pockets?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.71,0:24:31.09,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这要花上好长时间\NThis would take years.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.71,0:24:34.08,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,几十年去测试和研发\NDecades to test and develop...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.59,0:24:37.48,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,还得有一个能打败法拉利的赛车团队\Na race team capable of taking out Ferrari.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.48,0:24:38.71,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,法拉利破产了\NFerrari's bankrupt.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.10,0:24:45.01,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,恩佐把他赚到的每一分钱都花在追求完美上了\NEnzo has spent every lira he's got chasing perfection,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.01,0:24:46.17,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,而您猜怎么着\Nand you know something?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.21,0:24:47.14,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他做到了\NHe got there.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.03,0:24:49.12,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,但如今他破产了\NBut now he's broke.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.51,0:25:04.14,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,扣押
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.13,0:25:15.23,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你不必放弃赛车\NYou don't have to give up racing
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.23,0:25:16.68,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,去找一份正职  肯\Nto get a bloody day job, Ken.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.68,0:25:17.42,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我觉得有必要\NI think I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.85,0:25:18.81,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我已经玩够了\NNow, I've had my fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.81,0:25:20.33,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,是时候供养家庭\NIt's time to put food on the table...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.33,0:25:22.05,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,成长起来了\Nand grow up.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.22,0:25:23.72,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,修车店无法支撑我们支付账单\NThe garage didn't pay the bills.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.72,0:25:24.88,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,而且如今还被扣押了\NNow it's locked up.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.88,0:25:26.53,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,赛车同样也不能帮我们付账单\NRacing doesn't pay them either,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.53,0:25:27.71,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,更别说我还总是赢呢\Nand I keep winning.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.71,0:25:28.89,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,对啊  因为你很厉害\NYeah, because you're good.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.89,0:25:31.97,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,但我不太遵守规则\NBut I can't play the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.97,0:25:34.39,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我不是那种善于团队合作的人\NI'm not what they call a people person.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.39,0:25:36.42,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-这可不一定  -而且我已经45岁了\N- You don't say. - And I'm 45 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.42,0:25:38.01,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你真觉得我还会有所改变吗\NDo you really think I'm gonna change?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.01,0:25:41.11,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我永远也不会有什么很好的发展了\NI'm never gonna get the good rise.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.11,0:25:42.15,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我开始得太晚了\NI started too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.15,0:25:44.25,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,那是因为你参战了\NBecause you fought in the bloody war.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.65,0:25:49.47,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,如果你不赛车了  你会变得让人难以忍受的\NIf you stop, you'll be bloody insufferable.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.36,0:25:53.46,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我们别再绕圈子了  已经结束了\NLet's quit going round the Wrekin. It's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.92,0:25:55.65,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,想想好的那面\NLet's look on the bright side.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.69,0:25:57.04,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,如今我可以养老享福\NNow I can get fat and old,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.04,0:25:59.52,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,养养玫瑰  吃吃猪肉派\Ntrim the roses, and eat pork pies.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.79,0:26:05.69,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,法拉利
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.26,0:26:22.18,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,不好意思\NScusa.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.37,0:26:24.07,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,拜托  不能拍照\NPlease, no photos.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.07,0:26:24.84,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,拜托了\NPrego.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.10,0:26:27.31,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-放松点  -你得理解\N- Relax, will you? - You gotta understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.31,0:26:28.56,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这就像是黑手党出现\NThis is like the Mafia showing up
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.56,0:26:30.27,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,要买走自由女神像\Nto buy the Statue of Liberty.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.27,0:26:31.73,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,如今是反过来的\NKind of the opposite, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.90,0:26:35.23,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,如果媒体得到风声  就要出大乱子了\NThe press gets wind of this, the shit will hit the Fangio.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.50,0:26:37.47,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,李·艾亚科卡  福特汽车\NLee Iacocca, Ford Motor.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.47,0:26:39.50,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,弗兰科·格兹  法拉利\NFranco Gozzi, Ferrari.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.21,0:26:42.75,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,那是记者吗\NJournalists?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.75,0:26:44.37,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,不不  艾亚科卡先生  不是的\NNo, no, Mr. Iacocca, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.63,0:26:46.01,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,那是我们的摄影师\NIt's our cameras.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.27,0:26:47.53,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,只是为了见证历史\NJust for history.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.63,0:26:52.64,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,4L科伦坡发动机\NFour-liter Colombo engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.32,0:26:58.15,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,每个发动机都由一个人独立组装完成\NOne man assembles the entire engine by himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.89,0:27:03.07,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,变速器由另一个人组装\NAnother man assembles the transmission.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.88,0:27:05.22,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,一切都是手工制造\NEverything hand-built.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.28,0:27:08.26,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,太漂亮了\NBellissimo.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.60,0:27:22.71,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,赛车部\NRacing Department.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.68,0:27:25.46,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,李\NLee.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.02,0:27:26.79,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,那位就是\NThat's him.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.27,0:27:36.03,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我们两个公司合并后会形成两个实体\NThis merger between our companies will form two entities.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.47,0:27:40.58,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,福特-法拉利\NFord-Ferrari,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.58,0:27:42.13,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,福特控股90%\N90 percent owned by Ford,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.14,0:27:43.85,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,控制所有产品\Nwho controls all production.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.84,0:27:52.15,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,第二  法拉利-福特  赛车团队\NSecondly, Ferrari-Ford, the race team,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.15,0:27:54.37,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,法拉利控股90%\N90 percent owned by Ferrari.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.26,0:28:03.60,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,为了办妥这事  福特将支付...\NIn order to secure this, Ford will pay the sum...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.32,0:28:32.23,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,失陪\NExcuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.40,0:28:39.85,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他需要一点时间来读这份合同\NHe will need some time to read this.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.41,0:28:41.12,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,请便\NPlease.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.19,0:28:45.25,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,好的  当然了\NYeah, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.91,0:29:07.96,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我要找菲亚特的董事长
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.17,0:29:09.96,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,阿涅利
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.67,0:29:12.88,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我有照片要给你看
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.34,0:29:21.22,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,快点\NPronto.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.54,0:29:23.53,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,快点\NPronto.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.26,0:29:24.35,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我在
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.56,0:29:28.94,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你有什么要说的吗
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.60,0:29:32.23,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,恩佐继续享有完全控制权
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.86,0:29:35.78,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,公司一千八百万卖给我
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.76,0:29:40.10,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,吃完了  谢谢\NAll done, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.19,0:29:56.97,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,"先生们\N"Gentlemen,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.97,0:29:58.48,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,只有一个小问题\Nonly one small question.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.48,0:30:00.14,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,有关我的赛车项目"\NIt concerns my race program."
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.55,0:30:12.02,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,"如果我想参加勒芒赛\N"If I wish to race Le Mans,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.02,0:30:14.62,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,而你们不希望我参加勒芒赛\Nand you do not wish for me to race Le Mans...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.63,0:30:16.54,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,那我们是参加还是不参加"\N"Do we or do we not go?"
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.31,0:30:28.54,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,听着  在这种可能性极小的情况下\NLook, in that highly unlikely scenario...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.64,0:30:31.14,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,如果我们无法达成一致...\Nif we just can't agree...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.14,0:30:32.46,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,那么  是的\Nthen, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.46,0:30:34.45,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我是说  不行\NI mean, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.42,0:30:36.49,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你是对的\NYou are correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.64,0:30:38.84,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你不能参加\NYou do not go.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.87,0:30:58.46,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,"我作为一名制造者\N"My integrity as a constructor,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.46,0:30:59.67,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,一个男人  一个意大利人\N"as a man, as an Italian,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.67,0:31:02.14,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,被你们的提案深深地侮辱了"\N"is deeply insulted by your proposal."
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.12,0:31:04.70,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,"滚回密歇根去"\N"Go back to Michigan."
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.45,0:31:11.28,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,"滚回你那庞大丑陋的工厂去"\N"Back to your big, ugly factory."
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.74,0:31:14.89,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,"滚回你那庞大丑陋的工厂\N"Back to your big, ugly factory,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.90,0:31:16.49,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,去制造丑陋的小汽车"\Nmaking its ugly, little cars."
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.03,0:31:25.77,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,"告诉你那顽固的老板\N"Tell your pigheaded boss that
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.77,0:31:28.72,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他这些自以为是的管理层\N"all his, uh, smug executives
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.72,0:31:31.97,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,都是一文不值的王八蛋"\N"are worthless sons of whores."
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.66,0:31:37.13,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,告诉他  他不是亨利·福特\NTell him he's not Henry Ford.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.57,0:31:41.00,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他是亨利·福特二世\NHe's Henry Ford II.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.45,0:31:45.03,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我饿了  我们去吃东西吧
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.75,0:31:59.85,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,底特律独立报\N菲亚特收购法拉利\N恩佐保留完全控制权  赛车部门保持独立\N福特遭拒绝
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.29,0:32:09.61,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他耍了我们\NHe played us.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.46,0:32:13.45,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,恩佐那个老家伙本来就没打算卖给我们\NOld Man Enzo had no intention of selling to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.02,0:32:16.89,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他是利用我们来抬价\NHe used us to up his price...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.32,0:32:20.15,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,让我们公司蒙羞  还侮辱了你的领导力\Nembarrass our company and insult your leadership.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.68,0:32:22.69,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,整件事从一开始就不是个好主意\NIt was a bad idea from the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.38,0:32:33.55,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他到底说了什么\NWhat exactly did he say?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.51,0:32:43.36,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他说福特制造丑陋的小汽车\NHe said Ford makes ugly little cars,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.37,0:32:45.01,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,还说我们的工厂...\Nand we make 'em...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.45,0:32:46.98,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,很丑陋\Nin an ugly factory.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.05,0:32:52.50,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他说我们的管理层都是王八蛋\NHe said our executives are sons of whores.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.85,0:32:56.97,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,说了我什么\NAbout me?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.22,0:33:00.79,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他说您胖  先生\NHe called you fat, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.64,0:33:04.75,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,顽固\NPigheaded.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.12,0:33:06.87,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,继续\NGo on.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.68,0:33:10.96,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他说您不是亨利·福特\NHe said you're not Henry Ford.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.63,0:33:13.61,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,您只是亨利·福特二世\NYou're Henry Ford II.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.75,0:33:39.64,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我要找到最好的工程师\NI want the best engineers.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.09,0:33:42.46,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,最好的车手\NThe best drivers.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.96,0:33:46.63,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我不在乎花费\NI don't care what it costs.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.06,0:33:51.78,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我们要造一辆赛车\NWe're gonna build a race car.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.48,0:33:59.33,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我们要把那个\NAnd we're gonna bury
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.33,0:34:01.23,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,浑身机油的意大利佬\Nthat goddamn greasy wop
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.23,0:34:05.10,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,深埋在勒芒终点线的百尺之下\N100 feet deep under the finish line at Le Mans.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.47,0:34:09.64,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我会亲自到场见证这一幕的\NAnd I will be there to watch it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.10,0:34:12.02,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,她们来了  快快快\NHere they come. Go, go, go, go.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.23,0:34:17.07,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,混蛋\NAssholes.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.07,0:34:18.00,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你们太可悲了\NYou're really pathetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.00,0:34:19.25,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,十分抱歉  美女们\NI'm so sorry, girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.25,0:34:20.04,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,查理\NCharlie!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.52,0:34:22.77,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,别成天冲着女孩子们扔爆竹了\NQuit throwing crackers at the girls all damn day.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.77,0:34:23.77,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,该死的\NGod damn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.11,0:34:25.19,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,需要我去处理吗\NDo I gotta deal with this?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.19,0:34:26.59,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,已经处理好了\NIt's already taken care of.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.18,0:34:28.99,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,抱歉\NSorry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.99,0:34:32.27,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,没错  289立方英寸的V8发动机\NSo, yeah, 289 cubic inch V8.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.27,0:34:33.04,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,牛逼\NFar out.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.07,0:34:35.41,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,大范围地改造了AC Ace跑车的前段\NExtensive rework of AC Ace's front end.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.41,0:34:37.49,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,配有更强的后差速器来应付扭矩\NAnd a stronger rear diff to handle the torque.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.49,0:34:39.13,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,它在402米加速赛里表现如何\NHow's she handle a quarter mile?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.66,0:34:41.83,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我不是让你去参加直线加速赛\NWell, now, I'm not saying you should go drag racing,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.83,0:34:43.94,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,但它跑402米用时13.6秒\Nbut a quarter mile's 13.6.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.27,0:34:44.88,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,没错\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.88,0:34:46.63,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-这样算快的吗  -非常快了\N- Is that good? - Oh, that's real good.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.63,0:34:49.46,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他这周之内把同一辆车卖了三遍了\NHe sold that same car three times this week.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.50,0:34:51.81,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-收现金吗  现金可以吗  -现金可以\N- You take cash? Is cash okay? - Cash is okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.81,0:34:52.33,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,没错  先生\NYeah, mister,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.33,0:34:54.29,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你刚给自己买了辆了不得的跑车\Nyou just bought yourself one hell of a sport car.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.29,0:34:55.06,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,好啊\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.19,0:34:58.91,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你猜怎么着  我得...  菲尔\NTell you what, I'm gonna... Phil!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.21,0:35:00.66,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我让我的同事来接待你\NI'm gonna pass you off to my colleague here.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.67,0:35:01.83,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他会好好招呼你的\NHe gonna take care of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.83,0:35:03.14,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-菲尔  这位是怀亚特  -你好\N- Phil, Wyatt. - Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.14,0:35:05.38,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,怀亚特  我把他借走一下\NWyatt, I'm gonna steal him for one second.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.56,0:35:07.63,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你来收钱\NYou take the payment.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.70,0:35:09.59,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,无论你用什么方法  别让他把车开走\NWhatever you do, do not let him take that car.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.59,0:35:10.89,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,那是杰夫·布利策的车\NThat's Jeff Blitzer's car.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.89,0:35:13.16,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,也是弗兰克·柯林斯和史蒂夫·麦奎恩的车\NAnd Frank Collins' and Steve McQueen's.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.16,0:35:15.34,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,该死  我忘了麦奎恩了\NShit. I forgot about McQueen.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.48,0:35:19.21,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,早上好\NMorning.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.46,0:35:21.20,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,有什么事吗\NCan I help you?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.46,0:35:23.39,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,卡罗尔·谢尔比\NCarroll Shelby?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.89,0:35:25.65,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,也许吧\NMaybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.24,0:35:29.36,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,李·艾亚科卡  福特汽车\NLee Iacocca, Ford Motor.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.67,0:35:33.91,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这个扳手有什么故事\NWhat's with the wrench?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.99,0:35:36.96,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,那个啊  说来话长了\NThat? Oh, long story.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.79,0:35:40.92,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我们这里越做越大了  李\NWe are just going from strength to strength here, Lee.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.25,0:35:43.98,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,销售额亮眼  赛道上成绩斐然\NTerrific sales, we're killing it on the track.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.98,0:35:45.57,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我知道上一批发动机的钱\NNow, I know I owe Ford
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.57,0:35:46.58,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我还没给福特...\Nfor that last batch of engines...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.58,0:35:48.25,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,谢尔比先生  你放心\NMr. Shelby, I can assure you
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.25,0:35:49.39,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我来这里不是为了\NI'm not here for money
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.39,0:35:51.66,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你欠福特的那些零部件的钱\Nthat you might owe Ford for spare parts.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.81,0:35:53.55,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,不是为这个\NYou're not?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.77,0:35:56.37,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,不  不是的\NNo, I'm not.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.42,0:35:58.10,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,好吧\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.56,0:36:01.53,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我是代表福特先生来的  亨利·福特二世\NI'm here on behalf of Mr. Ford, Henry Ford II.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.53,0:36:04.17,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,如果  假设一下\NSuppose, um, hypothetically,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.17,0:36:06.14,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他希望他的公司\Nthat he wanted his company
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.14,0:36:09.00,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,能赢得勒芒24小时耐力赛\Nto win the 24 Hours of Le Mans.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.72,0:36:11.51,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你是少数赢过的美国人\NYou're one of the only Americans that's ever done it...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.51,0:36:14.05,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,所以我想知道\Nso I'm wondering...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.82,0:36:15.67,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,要付出什么努力\Nwhat's it take?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.42,0:36:20.62,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,假设吗\NHypothetically?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.79,0:36:22.79,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,假设\NHypothetically.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.45,0:36:26.36,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,要付出的努力是钱买不到的\NIt takes something money can't buy.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.49,0:36:28.93,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,钱可以买来速度\NMoney can buy speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.49,0:36:31.95,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,但与速度无关  李\NBut it isn't about speed, Lee.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.33,0:36:35.04,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,它不像其它的赛道\NIt's not just like those other tracks
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.05,0:36:38.65,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,只需要四个小时里不断左转\Nwhere all you do is turn to the left for four hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.82,0:36:42.26,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,要想赢  需要一辆车\NTo win that race, you need a car
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.26,0:36:44.56,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,足够轻  可以在直道上达到时速320公里\Nthat's light enough to do 200 on the straightaways
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.57,0:36:45.80,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,足够强  可以保持这个速度\Nbut strong enough to keep that up
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.80,0:36:48.31,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,连续跑近五千公里\Nfor 3,000 miles without a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.10,0:36:51.57,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,需要的不仅是\NNot just the best car
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.57,0:36:53.61,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你们制造过的最好的车  还要\Ny'all have ever made, but better than anything
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.61,0:36:55.94,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,比恩佐·法拉利当年参赛的车更好\Nthat Enzo Ferrari shows up with that year.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.94,0:36:57.43,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这还只是你的入场券\NAnd that just gets you to the green flag.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.43,0:36:59.34,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,接下来才是真正的问题\NThat's where your problems really start.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.53,0:37:03.03,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,没事吧\NIs everything okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.25,0:37:05.13,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,一边去\NGo away.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.42,0:37:14.17,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,所以你觉得有难度\NSo you're saying it's challenging.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.97,0:37:19.05,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,听着  那都不算是赛道  李\NLook, it's not even a track, Lee.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.76,0:37:22.26,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,勒芒是13.7公里的乡村道路\NLe Mans is eight and a half miles of country road.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.29,0:37:26.61,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,狭窄崎岖  很难开\NIt's narrow, ungraded, it's rough.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.75,0:37:29.91,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,转弯处没有预拱度  也没有栏杆\NThere's no camber on the turns, no rails.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.34,0:37:34.27,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,要开24小时\NYou gotta do that for 24 hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.91,0:37:37.39,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,24小时啊  李\NTwenty-four hours, Lee.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.45,0:37:40.68,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,也就是说包括夜晚\NThat means night.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.55,0:37:44.36,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,有一半的时间是夜里  屁都看不清\NHalf that race is in the dark. You can't see shit.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.02,0:37:47.90,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,时不时有车不知道从哪窜出来\NCars coming up on you out of nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.50,0:37:52.65,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,车手在赛道上出事  鲜血如注\NDrivers stumbling around the track, pouring blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.34,0:37:55.37,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,或许其中就有你的朋友  或许...\NMaybe one of 'em is your friend. Maybe...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.06,0:37:57.18,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,或许他身上会着火\NMaybe he's on fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.27,0:38:01.37,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你筋疲力尽  饥肠辘辘\NYou're exhausted, you're hungry...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.78,0:38:04.64,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,记不清自己的名字  忘记自己在哪\Ncan't remember your name, what country you're in.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.48,0:38:08.79,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,突然  你意识到自己正在直道上时速319公里\NAnd all of a sudden, you realize you're doing 198 on a straight.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.63,0:38:14.16,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,一旦有差错\NAnd if anything goes wrong...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.14,0:38:18.20,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,一个垫圈坏掉  只值五美分的垫圈\Nyou blow a gasket, a five-cent washer...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.41,0:38:20.13,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,那就完了  都结束了\Nthat's it, whole thing's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.09,0:38:22.34,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,法拉利又赢了\NFerrari wins again.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.51,0:38:26.07,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,就像去年和前年一样\NJust like he won last year and the year before that.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.19,0:38:27.47,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,还有大前年\NAnd the year before that.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.49,0:38:32.18,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,没错\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.51,0:38:34.65,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,有难度\NIt's challenging.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.78,0:38:37.41,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,所以你觉得\NSo you don't think...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.87,0:38:39.35,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,福特汽车公司无法造出\Nthat Ford Motor Company can build
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.36,0:38:41.63,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,有史以来最棒的赛车\Nthe greatest race car the world's ever seen?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.63,0:38:44.02,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你觉得我们无法\NYou think that we are incapable
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.41,0:38:46.10,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,赢得这样的比赛\Nof winning an event like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.24,0:38:48.47,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,即使我们有厉害的合伙人\NEven if we had a brilliant partner?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.22,0:38:54.68,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,即使我们有不设上限的预算\NEven if we wrote a, uh, blank check?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.30,0:39:04.85,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我说的是  你买不来冠军  李\NWhat I'm saying is, you can't buy a win, Lee.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.51,0:39:11.79,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,但或许你可以买来有机会夺冠的人\NBut maybe you could buy the guy who gets you a shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.62,0:39:29.38,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,修车店
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.43,0:39:32.76,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,换新的变速器  轮轴和减震器\NA new transmission, axles, shocks all around,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.76,0:39:36.16,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,把车身和轮胎都丢掉  这才有竞争力\Nditch the body and the tires, you have yourself a contender.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.30,0:39:39.09,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这宝贝里面还有正常的东西吗\NAnything on this beauty that does work?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.36,0:39:41.94,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,后视镜挺不错的\NThe mirrors are outstanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.94,0:39:43.43,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我走过来的时候就发现了\NI saw that walking up.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.41,0:39:48.82,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,所以你是晚上遛弯路过吗\NSo, what, you just passing on an evening stroll?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.11,0:39:51.81,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,斗牛犬  其实我有一份工作给你\NActually, Bulldog, I have a proposition for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.81,0:39:56.26,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你要造一辆能击败法拉利老爷子的车\NYou're gonna build a car to beat Old Man Ferrari...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.27,0:39:57.99,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-对  -和福特合作\N- Yeah. - ...with Ford?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.99,0:40:00.25,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,用福特的车\NWith a Ford?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.25,0:40:01.11,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,没错\NCorrect.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.58,0:40:03.60,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你告诉他们需要多长时间\NAnd how long did you tell them that you needed?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.60,0:40:05.39,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,两三百年吗\NTwo, three hundred years?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.79,0:40:06.81,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,九十天\NNinety days.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.91,0:40:14.67,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,好吧  我们来梳理一下\NAll right, so let's just look at this for a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.79,0:40:16.29,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,为了论证\NAnd for argument's sake,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.29,0:40:18.74,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我们先不提九十天这事\Nlet's just forget about the whole 90-day thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.75,0:40:20.41,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,所以先假设钱和时间\NSo let's just pretend you've got all the money in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.41,0:40:22.80,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,都应有尽有\Nand all the time in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.80,0:40:24.34,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-我喜欢这个开头  -好吧\N- I like the sound of that. - All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.34,0:40:25.37,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,那\NSo...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.15,0:40:29.17,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你觉得福特会让你\Nyou think that Ford are gonna let you build
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.81,0:40:33.05,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,按你的想法\Nthe car that you want...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.08,0:40:34.86,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,去造你想要的车吗\Nthe way you want it?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.86,0:40:38.04,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,那个福特汽车公司\NThe Ford Motor Company?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.01,0:40:40.39,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,那些人\NThose guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.41,0:40:42.44,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你去过底特律吗\NHave you ever been to Detroit?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.44,0:40:45.90,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他们有好几层都是律师\NThey have floors and floors of lawyers
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.90,0:40:47.72,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,有成千上万的营销人员\Nand millions of marketing guys,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.72,0:40:48.76,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他们都要和你见面\Nand they're all gonna want to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.76,0:40:50.12,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他们都要和伟大的卡罗尔·谢尔比\NThey're gonna want to get their photo taken
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.13,0:40:51.48,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,一起合影\Nwith the great Carroll Shelby,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.48,0:40:52.32,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他们会拍你马屁\Nand they're gonna kiss your ass
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.32,0:40:54.65,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,然后回到他们温馨的办公室里\Nand go back to their lovely offices...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.79,0:40:56.94,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,想出新的办法来搞你\Nand they're gonna work out new ways to screw you.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.94,0:40:59.68,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,为什么  因为他们不由自主\NWhy? Because they can't help it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.68,0:41:01.34,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,因为他们想要让老板高兴\NBecause they just want to please their boss
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.34,0:41:04.79,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,而他们的老板想要让自己的老板高兴  依次类推\Nwho wants please his boss who wants to please his boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.30,0:41:07.50,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他们为此而厌恶自己\NAnd they hate themselves for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.51,0:41:09.08,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,但在心底里\NBut deep down...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.27,0:41:11.29,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他们更厌恶的\Nwho they hate even more
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.33,0:41:12.60,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,是你这样的人\Nare guys like you,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.60,0:41:14.03,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,因为你与他们不同\Nbecause you're not like them,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.03,0:41:15.70,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,因为你与他们思考的方式不同\Nbecause you don't think like them,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.71,0:41:17.71,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,因为你不一样\Nbecause you're different.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.23,0:41:20.87,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这是大魔王的意思\NIt's coming straight from the Deuce.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.23,0:41:20.87,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,亨利·福特二世绰号"汉克大魔王"
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.51,0:41:24.61,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他是认真的\NHe's serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.90,0:41:26.52,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他们会真金白银地支持\NThey're gonna put real money behind it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.70,0:41:30.83,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我敢说是的\NI'll bet they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.99,0:41:32.90,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你知道为什么吗\NYou know why?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.47,0:41:36.48,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,因为有人  我没说是谁\NBecause someone, and I'm not saying who,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.48,0:41:42.35,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,有人告诉他们这是可能做成的\Nsomeone has told them that this is actually possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.67,0:41:43.46,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,听我说\NLook...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.46,0:41:45.15,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这周日在科洛弗\Nthis Sunday at Cloverfield,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.15,0:41:46.44,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他们会发布新的野马汽车\Nthey're launching the new Mustang.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.44,0:41:48.29,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,并宣布赛车项目\NThey're gonna announce the race program.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.37,0:41:50.59,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,来看看吧\NJust come on by.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.88,0:41:55.79,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,来看看  听听我的演讲\NCome take a look. Listen to my speech.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.26,0:41:57.43,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我会发表演讲\NI'm making a speech.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.56,0:41:58.92,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,带彼得来吧  他会喜欢的\NBring Peter. He'll love it.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.07,0:42:02.11,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,好吧  谢尔\NAll right, Shel.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.36,0:42:06.26,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,周日见\NSee you Sunday.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.47,0:42:15.32,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,爸爸  看啊\NDad, look at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.25,0:42:22.03,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,野马
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.73,0:42:21.46,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,福特野马  你觉得怎么样\NThe Ford Mustang. What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.86,0:42:26.88,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我觉得这是秘书开的车\NI think it's a secretary's car.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.54,0:42:29.92,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我喜欢\NI like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.73,0:42:34.58,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,抱...抱歉\NExcu... Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.31,0:42:38.07,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,请你  请你不要那么做\NWould you, would you not do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.89,0:42:40.67,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,对不起\NSorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.86,0:42:46.97,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他是  他是你儿子吗\NIs this, is this your son?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.17,0:42:48.20,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,是的\NYes, it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.50,0:42:51.80,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,能请你让他别碰车吗\NWould you ask him to keep his hands off the paintwork?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.82,0:42:52.72,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,没事  没事  彼得\NNo, no, no, Peter.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.73,0:42:54.29,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,没关系  你是谁\NYou're okay. Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.87,0:42:58.26,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,里奥·毕比  福特汽车公司的高级执行副总裁\NLeo Beebe, Senior Executive Vice President, Ford Motor Company.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.26,0:43:01.04,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我负责野马的发布\NI'm responsible for the launch of the Mustang.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.57,0:43:03.99,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,至少我们知道这是谁的责任了\NAt least now we know who's responsible.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.99,0:43:05.19,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,别理解错了  莱尼\NDon't get me wrong, Lenny.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.19,0:43:08.00,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-是里奥  -车看起来很不错\N- Leo. - It looks fantastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.00,0:43:10.22,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,但内部太繁琐了\NBut inside, it's a lump of lard
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.22,0:43:11.48,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,花里胡哨的  糊弄普通人\Ndressed up to fool the public.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.48,0:43:13.41,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我的建议是\NMy advice is,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.41,0:43:16.51,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,缩减直列六缸发动机和白痴的三档加速\Nlose the inline-six and that idiotic three-speed,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.51,0:43:20.25,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,缩短轴距  就能减轻半吨重量\Nshorten the wheelbase, somehow lose half a ton,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.44,0:43:21.81,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,还能降低成本\Nand lower the price.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.81,0:43:22.42,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,爸爸\NDad.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.42,0:43:23.63,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,但就算是那样\NBut even then,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.79,0:43:26.43,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我也更愿意买雪佛兰\NI'd still choose a Chevy Chevelle.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.83,0:43:29.58,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,而那辆车可是烂得不行\NAnd that's a fucking terrible car.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.57,0:43:32.40,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,怎么样了  史蒂夫\NHow are we doing up there, Steve?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.73,0:43:34.77,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,科洛弗到了  谢尔比先生\NThere's Cloverfield, Mr. Shelby.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.82,0:43:36.53,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,是啊\NOh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.28,0:43:39.47,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,介意我试一试着陆吗\NYou mind if I take a shot at the landing?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.40,0:43:41.13,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,不不不  我没开玩笑\NNo, no, no. I mean it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.13,0:43:44.02,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我1944年在圣安东尼奥开过B29轰炸机\NI flew B-29s out of San Antone in '44.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.02,0:43:44.97,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你在开玩笑吧\NYou're kidding.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.00,0:43:47.10,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-没骗你  -好吧\N- I did. - Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.10,0:43:48.22,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,卡罗尔  你做什么呢\NCarroll, what are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.61,0:43:50.01,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-他会开飞机吗  -卡罗尔\N- Does he know how to fly? - Carroll.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.01,0:43:52.46,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我以前有位指导员告诉我...\NI had an instructor tell me, he said...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.46,0:43:54.95,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,唐  我看现在最好系好安全带\NDon, I would say it's probably a good time to buckle up.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.95,0:43:57.00,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,"为了大家好  别上天了"\N"...do everybody a favor, stay on the ground."
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.86,0:43:59.21,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我说真的\NThat's a true story.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.49,0:44:00.70,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-不  -该死\N- Oh, no. - Oh, shit.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.70,0:44:02.50,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-该死的  -开始了\N- God damn it. - Here we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.46,0:44:09.07,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,野马
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.51,0:44:03.54,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这是一辆\NThis is the car
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.54,0:44:05.79,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你想不到会出自底特律的车\Nyou never expected from Detroit.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.79,0:44:11.13,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,好了  走吧\NAll right. Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.40,0:44:14.89,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,不留下来吗  肯\NNot staying, Ken?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.72,0:44:17.91,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,都他妈是冲动消费  对吧\NAh, it's a bloody pig in a poke, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.91,0:44:19.01,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他们来了\NHere they come now.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.86,0:44:26.39,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-等等  他们要坠毁了吗  -我的天\N- Wait. Are they crashing? - Oh, Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.54,0:44:27.76,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,飞行员是谁\NWho's the pilot?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.18,0:44:29.79,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,要我猜的话  彼得\NMy guess, Peter...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.24,0:44:34.59,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,是我们认识的人\Nit's someone we know.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.83,0:44:37.71,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,一切都还好吗\NEverything all right up there?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.80,0:44:38.74,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,不\NOh, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.12,0:44:40.65,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-不  -坐好了\N- No! - Hang on.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.65,0:44:44.06,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,该死  该死  该死\NOh, shit. Shit. Shit. Shit.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.06,0:44:47.02,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,该死  该死  该死\NShit. Shit. Shit.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.02,0:44:49.17,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,知道吗  就像骑自行车一样\NTell you what, that's like riding a bike.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.42,0:44:57.05,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这出场的仗势真不小\NTalk about making an entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.05,0:44:58.44,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-谢尔比  -我的天\N- Shelby... - Good grief.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.79,0:45:00.11,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-谢尔比  -好了\N- Shelby! - All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.11,0:45:02.19,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-看这里  看这里  -谢尔比\N- Over here. Over here! - Shelby!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.55,0:45:03.73,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你们好啊\NHow y'all doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.75,0:45:05.06,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,能给我签个名吗\NCan I get your autograph, please?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.06,0:45:06.42,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,能给我签个名吗  先生\NCan I get your autograph, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.46,0:45:07.95,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,卡罗尔  这是罗伊·朗恩\NCarroll, this is Roy Lunn.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.95,0:45:09.15,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,老罗伊是来这里研发\NOld Roy here is developing
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.15,0:45:10.53,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,英国设计的原型\Nthe prototype over in England.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.53,0:45:12.71,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我认识罗伊  幸会  罗伊\NOh, hell, I know Roy. Good to see you, Roy.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.71,0:45:13.96,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,欢迎来到疯人院  谢尔比\NWelcome to the madhouse, Shelby.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.96,0:45:15.73,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,福特出动了整个管理层\NFord wheeled out the entire executive committee
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.73,0:45:16.52,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,来参加这一盛会\Nfor this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.89,0:45:17.84,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,稍等一下\NHold that thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.61,0:45:21.45,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你好  飞行家先生\NHello, Mr. Lindbergh.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.77,0:45:23.80,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你喜欢吗  彼得  你好\NYou like that? Hey, Peter, how you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.80,0:45:25.02,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-谢尔比先生  -很高兴见到你\N- Mr. Shelby. - Good to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.02,0:45:28.07,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你要造一辆打败法拉利的车吗\NAre you building a car that's gonna beat Ferrari?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.30,0:45:31.16,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我们要参加勒芒耐力赛  这是肯定的\NWell, we're gonna go to Le Mans, that's for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.16,0:45:33.32,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,如果我们先冲过了终点线  那就会赢\NAnd if we get across that finish line first, we're gonna win.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.32,0:45:35.32,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,卡罗尔  我向你介绍里奥·毕比\NCarroll, allow me to introduce Leo Beebe,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.32,0:45:37.39,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,福特汽车的高级副总裁\NSenior Vce President, Ford Motor.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.67,0:45:39.04,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,好的  幸会  毕比先生\NOh, sure. Yeah. A pleasure, Mr. Beebe.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.04,0:45:40.62,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-感谢你光临  -认识一下肯·迈尔斯\N- Thank you for coming. - Say hello to Ken Miles
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.62,0:45:41.89,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-和他儿子彼得吧  -好\N- and his son, Peter. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.91,0:45:44.72,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-我们...我们见过了  -我们...我们见过了\N- We've, um... we met. - We, uh... we met.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.26,0:45:46.03,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,是啊\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.13,0:45:48.05,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,不是吗\NDidn't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.16,0:45:50.65,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,所以...\NSo, um, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.69,0:45:53.16,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我带彼得去卫生间\NI'll take Petey for some pop.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.31,0:45:54.87,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,祝你和这些人相处愉快  谢尔\NGood luck with these guys, Shel.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.23,0:45:57.33,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-再见  谢尔比先生  -再见  彼得\N- Bye, Mr. Shelby. - See you, Pete.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.65,0:45:59.34,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,别担心  他会留下来的\NDon't worry, he's gonna stay.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.39,0:46:02.98,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你们俩在飞机上有聊几句吗\NSo, you two get a chance to talk on the plane?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.09,0:46:05.56,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,有\NYeah. Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.58,0:46:08.70,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,卡罗尔  我们借一步说话\NCarroll, why don't we just step this way for a second?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.26,0:46:17.40,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这是惯例  走个过场\NLook, it's pro forma. It's window dressing.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.40,0:46:19.03,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,但在你得表现得有来有往\NBut there's gotta be a sense of give-and-take
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.03,0:46:20.48,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,和那些...\Nbetween you and...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.48,0:46:21.26,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你懂的\Nyou know.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.95,0:46:22.89,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我不懂\NNo, I don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.97,0:46:23.71,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,团队\NThe group.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.18,0:46:24.99,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,团队\NThe group?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.41,0:46:26.95,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,高级创意总监们  卡罗尔\NSenior creatives, Carroll.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.95,0:46:29.03,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,就是为了让大家都自在些\NJust to make sure everybody's comfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.55,0:46:30.73,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我很困惑  李\NWell, I'm confused, Lee.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.73,0:46:32.21,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,因为直到这一刻  直到刚刚\N'Cause up until this moment, right now,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.21,0:46:33.52,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我都还挺自在的\NI was comfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.66,0:46:36.67,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你应该往外看看  卡罗尔\NYou should take a look out there, Carroll.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.79,0:46:37.64,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你看到了什么\NWhat do you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.62,0:46:39.66,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你知道我看到了什么吗\NYou know what I see?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.94,0:46:41.21,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我看到了一个机器\NI see a machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.40,0:46:43.58,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我看到了一万个活动的零件\NI see 10,000 moving parts,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.58,0:46:44.90,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,希望能够和谐地运转\Nmoving hopefully in harmony,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.90,0:46:46.59,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,而这也是我的职责\Nand it's my job to make it so.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.59,0:46:47.93,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,指导你在其中和谐运转是我的职责\NIt's my job to guide you through it.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.93,0:46:50.20,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我是来这里帮你的  卡罗尔\NI am here to help you, Carroll.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.20,0:46:51.52,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,但你得信任我\NBut you gotta trust me.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.59,0:46:54.31,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-失陪了  李  -卡罗尔\N- Excuse me, Lee. - Carroll...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.69,0:46:56.89,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,如果你不信任我  就不要走上台\Ndo not step on that stage if you don't trust me.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.89,0:46:59.47,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,有请卡罗尔·谢尔比先生\NPlease welcome Mr. Carroll Shelby.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.47,0:47:00.18,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,得走了\NGotta go.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.79,0:47:06.73,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-谢尔比  -谢尔比\N- Shelby... - Oh. Shelby.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.71,0:47:08.64,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他说什么了\NWhat'd he say?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.86,0:47:09.91,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他知道流程\NHe gets the drill.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.95,0:47:14.91,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,福特野马
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.25,0:47:14.06,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,谢谢\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.14,0:47:16.83,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,要是我爸今天在这里\NWell, if my daddy was here today...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.47,0:47:18.64,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他会让我坐下\Nhe'd tell me to sit on down
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.64,0:47:20.91,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,让那些大学生来负责滔滔不绝\Nand leave the yakking to the college boys...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.91,0:47:24.84,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,所以  就像我开车一样  我会尽快讲完\Nso, like my cars, I'll make this fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.95,0:47:30.01,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我十岁时  爸爸告诉我"儿子...\NWhen I was 10 years old, Pops said to me, "Son...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.29,0:47:34.08,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,清楚自己想做什么的人是很幸运的\NIt's a truly lucky man who knows what he wants to do in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.60,0:47:36.72,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,因为他这辈子做事都会乐在其中"\N"'Cause that man will never work a day in his life."
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.70,0:47:40.39,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,但也有一小撮人  珍贵的一小撮人\NBut there are a few, a precious few,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.39,0:47:42.73,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我不知道他们幸运与否\Nand, hell, I don't know if they're lucky or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.44,0:47:44.58,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,但有一小撮人\NBut there are a few people
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.58,0:47:46.41,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,找到了自己必须要做的事\Nwho find something they have to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.63,0:47:49.59,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他们为之沉迷的事\NSomething obsesses 'em.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.52,0:47:52.15,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,如果不去做那件事\NSomething that if they can't do it,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.25,0:47:54.35,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他们就会被逼疯\Nit's gonna drive them clean out of their mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.33,0:47:56.26,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我就是那种人\NI'm that guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.71,0:48:00.44,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我知道还有一个人也有同感\NAnd I know one other man feels exactly the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.80,0:48:02.69,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他就是...\NHis name...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.42,0:48:07.03,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他就是亨利·福特先生\NHis name is Mr. Henry Ford.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.97,0:48:13.68,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,并且我们会一起\NAnd together, we're gonna build
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.68,0:48:15.92,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,制造出世界上速度最快的汽车\Nthe fastest automobiles in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.18,0:48:22.26,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我们也会在勒芒耐力赛中创造历史\NAnd we're gonna make history, too, at Le Mans.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.81,0:48:26.88,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-我们走  -什么\N- Let's go. - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.61,0:48:29.01,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我叫卡罗尔·谢尔比\NMy name is Carroll Shelby.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.90,0:48:31.26,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我制造赛车\NI build race cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.76,0:48:56.46,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,不  不管是什么  都不要\NNo. Whatever it is, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.85,0:48:59.50,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,不\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.93,0:49:01.79,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,三十分钟\NThirty minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.23,0:49:05.35,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我很累\NAh, just... I'm spent.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.35,0:49:07.59,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-我想洗个澡  - 你会想看看这个的\N- I wanna have a bath. - You're gonna wanna see this.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.40,0:49:09.05,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,相信我\NTrust me.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.19,0:49:13.26,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,三十分钟  然后送你回来吃肉汁烘肉卷\NThirty minutes. I'll have you back for meatloaf and gravy.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.70,0:49:17.89,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,三十分钟\NThirty minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.07,0:49:18.69,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,对\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.59,0:49:35.22,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,谢尔比美国公司
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.84,0:49:39.17,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,见鬼\NBloody hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.20,0:49:46.92,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,刚从英国空运过来\NFresh off the plane from England.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.02,0:49:52.76,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,它还没有完全调配好\NNow, she's still a little on the rare side of cooked.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.08,0:50:03.86,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,来吧\NCome on.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.88,0:50:17.70,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,有意思\NInteresting.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.24,0:50:35.89,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,怎样\NWell?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.36,0:50:37.06,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,很糟糕\NIt's awful.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.49,0:50:38.78,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,比糟糕还要糟\NIt's worse than awful.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.78,0:50:40.10,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这车抓地力太差\NYeah, it doesn't track.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.20,0:50:42.52,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,三档太高了\NYou know, the third gear is too high.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.54,0:50:46.11,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,扭矩碰不到路面\NTorque is not reaching the road.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.25,0:50:50.25,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,因为前端太轻  转向装置不敏感\NSteering's loose because the front end gets light.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.25,0:50:52.86,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,并且速度超过225公里  它就成了...\NAnd over 140, it thinks it's a...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.04,0:50:53.84,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,飞机\NAirplane.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.84,0:50:54.41,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,对\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.05,0:50:57.08,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,它想起飞去夏威夷\NIt wants to lift off and fly to Hawaii.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.93,0:51:00.87,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,还有吗\NAnything else?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.06,0:51:07.75,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,等一下\NOne sec.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.84,0:51:40.33,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你昨晚回来很晚\NYou were back late last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.55,0:51:41.20,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,对\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.31,0:51:46.21,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你是在工作吗\NWere you working?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.02,0:51:52.42,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你没去别的地方\NSo, you didn't go anyplace?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.44,0:51:53.97,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,什么\NWhat?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.52,0:51:59.14,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我是问  你昨晚没去其它地方吗\NWell, I'm asking, did you go anyplace last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.45,0:52:02.06,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,莫莉\NMollie.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.86,0:52:04.35,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这是个简单的问题\NIt's a simple question.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.04,0:52:08.15,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我也回答了  不是吗\NAnd I answered, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.95,0:52:09.94,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,回答是什么\NWhat was the answer?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.42,0:52:13.49,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,出了什么事吗  亲爱的\NIs something up, love?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.75,0:52:17.34,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你在做什么  你在做什么\NWhat are you doing? What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.34,0:52:19.09,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你开得特别快\NYou're driving very fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.09,0:52:20.45,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,是吗  是吗\NOh, am I? Am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.76,0:52:21.79,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你就是\NYes, you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.97,0:52:26.04,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,见鬼  你这是...这是做什么\NBloody hell! What are you... the hell is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.39,0:52:28.10,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你告诉我  因为我不知道\NWell, you tell me, 'cause I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.10,0:52:30.17,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,行  开慢点\NRight, slow down!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.31,0:52:32.00,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,莫莉\NMollie!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.69,0:52:36.98,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,请你开慢点  好吗\NPlease slow it down, all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.98,0:52:38.65,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你想杀了我们还是怎样\NYou trying to kill us or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.65,0:52:40.93,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-我还以为我们喜欢这样呢  -什么\N- Well, I thought we love this shit. - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.70,0:52:45.24,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-见鬼  -这就是赛车的快感  不是吗\N- Bloody hell! - It's a bit of racing fun. No?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.24,0:52:46.89,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,不不不  完全不一样\NNo, no, no. It's not the same at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.08,0:52:48.60,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我还以为很刺激呢\NWell, I think it's thrilling!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.37,0:52:50.15,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,行\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.08,0:52:52.86,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我看到你了  行吗\NLook, I saw you, all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.83,0:52:56.63,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我看见你和谢尔比一起离开  我看到你回来\NI saw you leaving with Shelby, and I saw you coming back.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.63,0:52:58.63,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,好  见鬼  行  你慢点\NOkay. Shit. Okay, but slow it...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.63,0:53:00.50,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,然后你就保持这种傻乎乎的表情一整天了\NAnd then all day you've got that stupid look on your face.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.51,0:53:02.95,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,莫莉  开慢点  你离得太近了\NMollie, slow down. You're too close here.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.80,0:53:08.35,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,莫莉  赶紧踩刹车\NMollie, put on the brakes right now...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.35,0:53:10.56,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你不告诉我出了什么事  我就不停\NNot until you tell me what's going on!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.56,0:53:13.10,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,行  我去看了一辆车\NAll right. I went to look at a car.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.10,0:53:15.01,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-和谢尔比一起  -和谢尔比一起\N- With Shelby? - With Shelby.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.06,0:53:17.05,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-一辆赛车  -差不多吧\N- A racing car? - Sort of.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.44,0:53:20.43,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,要转弯了  你最好抓紧点\NThere's a corner coming. You'd better hold on.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.03,0:53:24.53,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你准备一直踩着油门吗\NAre you gonna lift your foot off at all through this?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.53,0:53:26.15,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,对  因为我喜欢干净利落的比赛路线\NNo, 'cause I like a clean racing line.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.16,0:53:27.39,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,慢点\NSlow down!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.54,0:53:32.31,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,好吧\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.37,0:53:33.69,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,谢尔给了我一个工作\NShel offered me a job.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.87,0:53:37.42,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,福特有一辆想用来和法拉利比赛的车\NFord has a car that they want to put up against a Ferrari.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.42,0:53:39.13,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-你告诉我你不干了  -就是这样  现在慢点\NYou told me you were done. That's it. Now, slow...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.13,0:53:40.96,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我没同意\NI didn't say yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.96,0:53:42.13,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,慢点\NSlow down.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.13,0:53:43.62,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你告诉我你不干了\NYou told me you quit.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.84,0:53:47.04,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-我不懂  -养老享福  你说的\N- I don't understand. - Get fat and old, you said.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.59,0:53:48.75,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,养老享福\NFat and old.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.89,0:53:54.43,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-我不懂  -你是那么告诉我的\N- I don't understand. - That's what you told me.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.43,0:53:56.05,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我不懂\NI don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.23,0:53:57.85,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你生气是因为我说我不干了\NAre you upset because I said I was done
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.85,0:54:00.51,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,还是因为我看了一辆赛车\Nor because I looked at a race car?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.90,0:54:03.97,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,别对我说谎  肯\NJust don't lie to me, Ken.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.20,0:54:07.70,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,别因为你觉得我会高兴\NDon't make it a secret,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.70,0:54:09.24,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,就对你想要什么\Nwhat you want or what you feel,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.24,0:54:11.98,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你感觉如何  藏着掖着\Njust because you think it's gonna make me happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.08,0:54:16.07,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,莫  我都不知道我是什么感觉\NMoll, I don't even know what I feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.38,0:54:24.74,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,如果你要参赛\NIf you do this...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.72,0:54:29.66,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,那他这次最好给你钱\Nthen he better be paying you this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.14,0:54:35.35,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,因为我增加工作时间就没法照顾彼得\N'Cause I can't work any more hours and look after Peter.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.35,0:54:36.60,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,国税局已经封了修车店\NYou know, the IRS have the garage.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.60,0:54:38.76,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我不要再失去我的家\NI'm not losing my home.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.52,0:54:40.93,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,一天两百块\NIt's 200 a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.03,0:54:45.47,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,还报销开支\NPlus expenses.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.24,0:54:49.60,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你在跟我开玩笑吗\NAre you shitting me?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.07,0:54:52.23,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,但我还没有决定\NBut I haven't decided.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.12,0:54:56.69,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,一天两百美金\N$200 a day?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.46,0:55:00.57,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你疯了吗\NAre you nuts?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.50,0:55:08.13,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,柳泉赛道
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.07,0:55:27.07,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,看看这个  太离谱了  这里\NLook at this. This is ridiculous. Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.07,0:55:29.72,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,谢尔  它吸气\NSo, Shel, grabbing air.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.32,0:55:31.27,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这就是问题\NThat's the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.53,0:55:36.24,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,速度超过145公里  空气就只进不出\NOver 90, air's getting in, not getting out.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.24,0:55:38.29,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,问题在车头  我开的时候感觉到了\NIt's the nose, I can feel it in the wheel.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.29,0:55:39.62,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,迈尔斯先生  如果有问题\NMr. Miles, if there's a problem,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.62,0:55:40.65,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,电脑会发现的\Nthe computer will find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.83,0:55:41.86,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,行  查理\NAll right. Charlie,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.21,0:55:44.28,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,去拿点胶带和毛线\Nget some Scotch tape and a ball of wool.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.46,0:55:47.58,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,好了  很好\NAll right. Good, good, good.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.67,0:55:51.87,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,现在我们把这些垃圾拆掉\NSo, now let's just, uh, get all of this junk out.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.88,0:55:52.68,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,对吗  老爹\NRight, Pops?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.68,0:55:54.17,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,对对  我同意\NYeah, yeah. I concur.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.18,0:55:54.96,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,来吧  伙计们\NCome on, guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.14,0:55:59.04,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他们在做什么\NWhat are they doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.73,0:56:01.13,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,让你的车跑得更快些\NMaking your car faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.94,0:56:09.93,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这里  就这里\NThere. Right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.94,0:56:11.31,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,气流开始堵塞了\NAirflow's getting stuck.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.45,0:56:17.19,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我看到了  毛线直直往上飘\NI see it. Yarn blows straight up.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.33,0:56:18.52,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-对  -前面在飘高\N- Yep. - The front's lifting.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.74,0:56:19.77,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,见鬼  他说得对\NDamn, he's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.13,0:56:34.00,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这辆车想变得更快  我能感觉出来\NThis car wants to go faster. I feel it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.51,0:56:36.33,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,再轻点就会变得脆弱\NAny lighter, we're getting fragile.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.55,0:56:38.89,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,上星期它已经减重了三十公斤\NTook 70 pounds out of her in the last week.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.89,0:56:41.92,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,通过这次改装  它已经输出了最大马力了\NShe's outputting max horsepower from this displacement.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.60,0:56:43.98,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,那就换个更大的发动机\NSo put in a bigger engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.98,0:56:45.47,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我们要把发动机放在哪  车顶吗\NWhere we gonna put it? On the roof?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.11,0:56:50.40,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,设法让它比纳斯卡车赛标准\NManaged to make it 52 pounds lighter
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.40,0:56:52.14,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,轻了二十三公斤\Nthan the NASCAR unit.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.07,0:56:59.36,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,全新的铝制缸盖\NAll-new aluminum cylinder heads...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.29,0:57:03.57,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,减振器  水泵  更小的阀门\Nvibration dampeners, water pump, smaller valves.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.66,0:57:05.03,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我们称之为野兽\NWe call it the Beast.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.83,0:57:06.88,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我能看出原因\NYeah, I can see why,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.88,0:57:08.13,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,但不改装机座的话\Nbut how's it gonna fit
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.13,0:57:10.16,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,要怎么把它塞进去\Nwithout a redesign of the engine bed?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.42,0:57:11.59,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,那肯定不容易\NWell, it certainly wasn't easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.59,0:57:12.92,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,早安  先生们  谢尔比先生\NGood morning, gentlemen. Mr. Shelby.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.92,0:57:17.25,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你们已经把那个装进了一台GT40吗\NSo, you already put that in a GT40?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.01,0:57:19.21,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,恐怕确实如此\NI'm afraid we have.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.19,0:57:26.26,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,真想不到\NI'll be damned.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.31,0:57:28.48,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,当然  那很重\NWell, it's heavy, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.48,0:57:30.19,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,控制起来有点困难  特别是刹车\NProblems with the handling, especially the stopping.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.19,0:57:32.10,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-我能给你看数据  -有什么问题\N- I can show you the data. - What problems?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.49,0:57:33.74,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,转向有点失灵  但是...\NUndersteers a little, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.74,0:57:34.47,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我能借用一下那个吗\NCan I borrow that?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.20,0:57:36.60,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,就一下  谢谢\NJust a second. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.86,0:57:37.39,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,肯\NKen!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.45,0:57:41.70,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,肯  你在测试前要不要先和总部协商一下\NKen, perhaps you want to check with HQ before you test...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.70,0:57:42.44,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他说什么\NWhat did he say?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.75,0:57:43.73,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我们得问问...\NWe should ask...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.83,0:57:45.40,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,好吧\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.29,0:57:50.86,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,太棒了\NOh, yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.14,0:58:00.68,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,谢尔比先生  欢迎来到迪尔伯恩\NMr. Shelby, welcome to Dearborn.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.68,0:58:01.76,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你怎么想到来看试车\NWhat are you doing at a test track?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.76,0:58:04.13,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你的漂亮西装会沾上嘉实多汽油的\NYou're gonna get Castrol oil all over that nice suit.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.74,0:58:06.98,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我想听听你对一些计划中的决策有什么意见\NI wanted to hear your thoughts on a few planning decisions.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.98,0:58:08.47,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,关于勒芒耐力赛的参赛人员\NYou know, personnel for Le Mans.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.52,0:58:10.05,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我们阵容强大\NWell, it's a hell of a lineup.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.15,0:58:11.59,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,肯·迈尔斯  菲尔·希尔\NKen Miles, Phil Hill,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.02,0:58:13.90,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,克里斯·阿蒙  布鲁斯·迈凯轮\NChris Amon, Bruce McLaren.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.90,0:58:16.22,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,希尔去定了  阿蒙和迈凯轮也是\NHill's a lock. Amon, McLaren, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.36,0:58:17.81,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我们对迈尔斯参赛不太确定\NWe're less sure about Miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.07,0:58:19.52,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我们喜欢里奇·金瑟尔\NWe like Richie Ginther...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.03,0:58:22.56,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,马斯滕·格里高利  鲍勃·邦杜兰特\NMasten Gregory, Bob Bondurant.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.16,0:58:25.29,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你们想要最好的车手\NWell, you're gonna want the best driver for the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.29,0:58:26.61,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,懂车的车手\NUnderstands the machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.91,0:58:27.90,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,肯就是最佳人选\NThat's Ken.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.50,0:58:30.36,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,太棒了\NOh! Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.25,0:58:34.71,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,再给点劲  快  再给点劲  宝贝\NMore of that, please. More of that, my girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.71,0:58:36.88,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你或许比我更懂赛车  谢尔比先生\NI may not get the finer points of racing, Mr. Shelby,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.88,0:58:38.20,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,但我懂人\Nbut I do know people.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.88,0:58:39.79,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,迈尔斯是...\NMiles is a...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.51,0:58:42.96,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他属于"垮掉的一代"  从穿着看得出来\NWell, he's a beatnik. He dresses like one.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.93,0:58:45.59,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,福特象征着可靠\NFord means reliability.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.89,0:58:47.42,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,肯·迈尔斯无法代表福特的形象\NKen Miles is not a Ford man.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.62,0:58:51.76,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,加把劲  加把劲\NGiddy-up! Giddy-up!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.82,0:58:56.47,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,目前圈速纪录是多少  伯特\NWhat's the lap record here, Burt?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.86,0:58:57.85,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,1分58秒\N1:58.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.16,0:59:00.38,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他跑了1分50秒\N1:50 dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.38,0:59:01.60,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,"垮掉的一代"\NA beatnik?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.62,0:59:03.24,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,那个男人在诺曼底登陆战役中\NThat man landed a busted tank
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.24,0:59:04.28,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,开着一架故障坦克登陆沙滩\Non the beach at D-Day
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.29,0:59:06.27,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,然后顺利地横穿欧洲开到柏林\Nand drove it clean across Europe to Berlin.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.00,0:59:08.11,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这哪算"垮掉的一代"\NA beatnik?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.83,0:59:10.29,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,李不久前问我\NYou know, Lee here asked me a while back,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.29,0:59:12.03,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,"钱买不到的那样东西是什么"\N"What's the one thing money can't buy?"
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.13,0:59:14.28,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我告诉你答案\NI'll tell you what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.75,0:59:16.83,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,是把握方向盘的那个纯粹的赛车手\NA pure racer behind the wheel of your car.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.72,0:59:18.87,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,肯·迈尔斯便是\NThat's Ken Miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.84,0:59:22.33,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,话虽如此\NWell, be that as it may...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.43,0:59:25.17,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我们觉得他有点太纯粹了\Nwe think he may be too pure.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.23,0:59:36.35,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,卡罗尔  要顾全大局\NCarroll, do not lose sight of the big picture here.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.86,0:59:38.64,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,"太纯粹了"\N"Too pure"?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.99,0:59:41.23,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这是什么意思\NWhat exactly does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.45,0:59:43.98,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,意思是他太自我了\NIt means he's all about himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.79,0:59:47.79,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,美国广播公司采访他的时候\NABC puts a microphone under his nose,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.79,0:59:49.94,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,或许会有他不喜欢的细节\Nperhaps there's a detail he dislikes,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.16,0:59:51.24,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,届时有几百万观众...\Nmillions watching...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.42,0:59:53.67,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你确定他不会乱说话吗\Ndo you trust him not to put out the wrong message?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.67,0:59:55.17,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你们可以找个外表光鲜\NWell, look, you can get a clean-cut,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.17,0:59:56.38,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,上镜的典型美国小子\Nall-American poster boy
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.38,0:59:57.50,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,让他坐上赛车\Nand stick him behind the wheel,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.51,0:59:58.70,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,教他怎么说话\Nteach him what to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.01,1:00:00.63,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你们不如让多丽丝·戴参赛吧\NShit, you get Doris Day to drive the car,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.01,1:00:00.63,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,美国二战后著名歌手
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.63,1:00:02.00,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,如果你们想输的话\Nif all you want to do is lose.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.59,1:00:05.08,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,所以你在这件事上有不同意见\NSo, you don't agree with us on this issue?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.77,1:00:09.55,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我是说你得相信我的选人眼光\NI'm saying you gotta trust me on this one.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.68,1:00:11.98,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,卡罗尔  考虑到营销因素\NCarroll, with marketing concerns,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.98,1:00:13.30,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这不可能\Nthat's just not possible.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.36,1:00:17.46,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,选一个福特类型的车手开着福特车参赛\NPut a Ford-type driver in a Ford car,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.47,1:00:18.39,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,谢尔比先生\NMr. Shelby.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.36,1:00:20.60,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这是福特的做事方式\NThat's the Ford way.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.16,1:00:29.74,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,法拉利又赢下了一场锦标赛\NYet another championship win for Ferrari
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.75,1:00:31.62,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,英国赛车手约翰·瑟蒂斯\Nas British driver John Surtees
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.62,1:00:33.25,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,开着法拉利312...\Npilots his Ferrari 312...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.25,1:00:34.32,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,法拉利赢了\NFerrari wins.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.33,1:00:37.84,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这是瑟蒂斯自1964年以来的首场胜利...\NIt's Surtees' first win since the '64...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.84,1:00:39.59,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,楔木  我们有楔木了\NWedges. We have wedges.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.59,1:00:41.08,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,很好  很好\NOh, good, good, good.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.76,1:00:42.54,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,完美\NPerfect.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.88,1:00:45.58,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-一米吗  -对\N- 40? - Yep.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.06,1:00:56.52,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-你好  老板  -你好  丹\N- Hey, boss. - Hey, Dan.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.52,1:00:58.07,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,老板  法拉利刚刚拿下了...\NBoss, Ferrari just bagged...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.07,1:00:58.84,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你有护照吗\NYou got a passport?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.23,1:00:59.94,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,那是什么\NWhat's that?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.94,1:01:01.43,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,签字  申请一个护照\NSign that. Get a passport.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.74,1:01:03.70,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,周五前交给我  弗罗斯特\NGet it back to me by Friday. Frosty.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.70,1:01:05.14,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,伙计们  我要去法国了\NBoys, I'm going to France.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.20,1:01:07.94,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,菲尔\NPhil.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.45,1:01:09.81,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,肯  能谈谈吗\NKen, can I get a word?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.84,1:01:19.91,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我能留下这个吗\NCan I take this?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.96,1:01:25.09,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你知道为什么福特给车取名GT40吗\NDo you know why Ford named it the GT40?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.09,1:01:27.05,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,为什么是"40"\NWhy they put that "40" on there?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:27.05,1:01:29.10,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-不知道  -这是规定  知道吗\N- No. - Regulations. All right?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.10,1:01:31.42,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,车身要有40英寸[一米]高\NWe gotta be 40 inches high
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.72,1:01:34.67,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,才能满足离地间隙要求\Nto make the ground clearance requirements.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.73,1:01:35.69,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,不多不少\NNo more, no less.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:35.69,1:01:37.23,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他们在每场比赛前都会测量\NThey measure it before every race.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.23,1:01:40.18,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,问题是这么高的车身\NProblem is, that with that height,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.40,1:01:43.36,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,车底阻力太大了  对吧\Nthere's too much drag under the car, all right?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.36,1:01:45.06,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,所以我们想了个办法\NSo, we have a solution.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.20,1:01:46.86,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,楔木  我们把楔木放在\NWedges. We put wedges
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.86,1:01:48.44,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-悬挂上...  -你下周不能去\N- in the suspension... - You're not coming next week.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.49,1:01:52.86,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你不能去  肯\NYou're not coming, Ken.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.17,1:01:56.99,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我们会带上迈凯轮\NWe're taking McLaren,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.00,1:01:58.86,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,克里斯·阿蒙  菲尔·希尔...\NChris Amon, Phil Hill...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.13,1:02:01.41,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,还有鲍勃·邦杜兰特\Nand Bob Bondurant.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.50,1:02:03.53,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这是福特的决定\NIt's Ford's call.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.26,1:02:07.58,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他们认为你形象欠佳\NIt is their opinion that you are not a good image,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.72,1:02:09.67,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,所以你不能开福特赛车\Nso you cannot drive their race car.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.56,1:02:13.10,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,即使是你尽心尽力把赛车\NAnd putting aside the fact that you made that car
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.10,1:02:14.29,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,改造成现在这样...\Nwhatever the hell it is...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:15.31,1:02:18.38,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,而且你是我眼中最棒的赛车手\Nand you're the best man I got behind the wheel...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.96,1:02:40.08,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我会调整供油管路\NI'm gonna reroute the oil line.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.08,1:02:41.79,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,要是发生泄漏  汽油会滴到\NIf there's spillage, it could drip
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.79,1:02:44.53,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-制动盘的左后方  -肯...\N- onto the rear nearside disc. - Ken...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.71,1:02:45.96,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,告诉那些小子们\NTell the boys
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.97,1:02:50.21,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,全程注意车速\Nto watch their pace come sunrise.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:50.26,1:02:53.50,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,变速箱会过热\NThe, uh, the gearbox will overheat.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.85,1:03:03.32,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,环球航空公司
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.78,1:03:06.99,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,谢尔比美国公司
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.82,1:03:13.03,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,肯  比赛快开始了\NKen, the race is starting soon.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.03,1:03:14.10,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,要打开收音机吗\NWant it on the radio?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.58,1:03:15.73,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,不了  除非你想听\NNot unless you do.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.31,1:03:36.38,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,比赛\N...of the race.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:36.68,1:03:37.10,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他们来了\NThere they are.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.10,1:03:38.98,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,玛莎拉蒂进入了埃索斯连续弯\NThe Maserati going into the Esses,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.98,1:03:40.31,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,但依然是2号车\Nbut it's still the number 2 car,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.31,1:03:41.14,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,由克里斯·阿蒙驾驶\Ndriven by Chris Amon.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.15,1:03:44.89,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,第三名是布鲁斯·迈凯轮驾驶的福特1号\NIn third place is the number 1 Ford that is driven by Bruce McLaren.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.02,1:03:47.43,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,福特GT启动速度尤为惊人\NA tremendously fast start for the Ford GT.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.61,1:03:51.52,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,福特2号圈速3分43秒4\N3:43.4 lap for car number 2, a Ford.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:51.70,1:03:54.37,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我认为在比赛的这个阶段速度有点太快了\NI think it's a little bit quick for this stage of the game.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.37,1:03:55.45,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,现在有点开太快了\NLittle bit quick right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.45,1:03:56.52,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,开得太急了\NRacing too hot.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:58.62,1:04:00.78,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这能持续到最后大概一小时  你不觉得吗\NThis could go down to the last hour or so, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.83,1:04:02.17,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,或许可以  但是\NIt could, but the probabilities
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.17,1:04:03.17,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,在24小时耐力赛里\Nfor a finish like that
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.17,1:04:05.28,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,出现这种终场的可能性极小\Nin a 24-hour race are awfully small.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.67,1:04:07.38,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,又一辆福特进入了维修站\NAnother Ford has come into the pits.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.38,1:04:08.99,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,修理工把车推进了\NIt's being pushed into the pits
Dialogue: 0,1:04:09.51,1:04:10.95,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-维修站  -汽缸垫\N- by the mechanics. - Head gasket.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.01,1:04:13.83,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,赛车不是航天火箭\NThe car's not a moon rocket.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:13.97,1:04:16.67,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,七号车紧随鲍勃·邦杜兰特  位居第四\NTrailing Bob Bondurant in fourth, car number 7.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.71,1:04:19.84,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,随后是迈克尔·帕克斯驾驶的法拉利20号\NLeading number 20, Ferrari. Michael Parkes.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.14,1:04:22.19,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,所以目前福特包揽前三名  你怎么看\NSo, we have Ford running one, two, three. How about that?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:22.19,1:04:24.13,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,太快了  绝对太快了\NToo soon. Surely too soon.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.94,1:04:30.22,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,维修工真的非常值得尊重...\NOne has to really be respectful of the mechanism with any...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:42.33,1:04:43.57,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,有条大新闻\NHere's the big story,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.75,1:04:45.79,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,先前处于领先地位的里奇·金瑟尔驾驶的福特\Nthe lead Ford, driven by Richie Ginther,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.79,1:04:48.50,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,由于变速箱故障退出了  最新的领先者是...\Nretired with gearbox trouble, and the new leader...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.50,1:04:52.51,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,变速箱  我告诉过他们  一定要小心\NGearbox. I told them. Be gentle with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.51,1:04:54.18,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,和他的搭档洛伦佐·班迪尼\N...and his partner Lorenzo Bandini...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.18,1:04:56.79,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他是去年获奖车手之一\N...who was one of the winning drivers last year.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.51,1:04:59.21,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,是谁\NWho's there?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.56,1:05:02.35,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我们又回来了\NAgain, we're back,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.35,1:05:05.34,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,为您实时转播法国的勒芒赛事\Nspeaking to you live from Le Mans, France.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.44,1:05:08.23,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,勒芒24小时耐力赛  第33届国际汽车\NThe 24 Hours of Le Mans, the Grand Prix of Endurance,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.23,1:05:09.43,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,耐力大奖赛\Nthe 33rd renewal.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.73,1:05:12.18,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你在听什么广播\NWhat's that you're listening to?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.07,1:05:15.10,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,法国的一场比赛\NOh, some race over in France.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.58,1:05:19.44,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,很精彩吗\NExciting?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.29,1:05:22.07,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我没怎么听\NI'm not really paying much attention.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.33,1:05:25.07,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,然而  菲尔  回首1933年\NHowever, Phil, there was one time in 1933,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.17,1:05:28.11,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,领先者变化了三次\Nwhen the lead changed hands three times.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.55,1:05:33.99,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,♪ I ain't lyin' ♪
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.56,1:05:38.42,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,I Put a Spell on You - Nina Simone
Dialogue: 0,1:05:36.47,1:05:38.42,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,♪ No, I ain't lyin' ♪
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.22,1:05:41.75,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这不算是香槟...\NIt's not exactly champagne...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:41.56,1:05:43.46,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,♪ You know I can't stand it... ♪
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.10,1:05:46.21,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,但至少也有气泡\Nbut it's got bubbles.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.10,1:05:48.76,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,♪ You know better, daddy ♪
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.27,1:05:53.64,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,♪ I can't stand it 'cause you put me down ♪
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.82,1:05:55.64,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,♪ Yeah, yeah ♪
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.12,1:05:59.85,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,♪ I put a spell on you ♪
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.82,1:06:06.36,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,♪ Because you're mine ♪
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.17,1:06:11.45,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,♪ You're mine ♪
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.93,1:06:16.91,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,谢谢  莫莉\NThanks, Mollie.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.43,1:06:26.84,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,♪ Yeah, yeah ♪
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.68,1:06:30.30,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,♪ Oh, yeah ♪
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.36,1:06:41.45,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,福特汽车公司
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.62,1:06:43.70,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,底特律独立报\N福特惨败
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.58,1:06:53.03,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,福特和法拉利之间是有区别的\NThere's a difference between Ford and Ferrari...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.60,1:07:03.33,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,格蕾丝\NGrace.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.48,1:07:14.55,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,好的  先生  我马上带他进来\NYes, sir. I will send him right in.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.48,1:07:14.90,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,行政前台
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.65,1:07:16.18,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,谢谢\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.15,1:07:21.52,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,谢尔比先生  福特先生现在可以见你了\NMr. Shelby, Mr. Ford will see you now.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:22.37,1:07:23.82,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-好  -你还愿意\N- All right. - Are you still willing
Dialogue: 0,1:07:23.83,1:07:25.98,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,赌上名誉相信这个人吗\Nto stake your reputation on this guy?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.08,1:07:29.36,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这边请  谢尔比先生\NThis way, Mr. Shelby.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:39.68,1:07:40.58,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,福特先生\NMr. Ford.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.47,1:07:42.12,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,各位\NGentlemen.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.76,1:07:43.46,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,谢尔比\NShelby.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:56.86,1:07:59.86,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,给我一个理由  说服我不解雇\NGive me one reason why I don't fire everyone
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.86,1:08:02.93,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,由你牵头的这一群残兵败将\Nassociated with this abomination starting with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.66,1:08:10.44,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,先生\NWell, sir...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.12,1:08:13.87,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我坐在外面舒服的休息室里\NI was thinking about that very question
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.88,1:08:16.82,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,就在想这个问题\Nas I sat out there in your lovely waiting room.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:18.67,1:08:19.59,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,当我坐在那里\NAs I was sitting there...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.59,1:08:23.37,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我看见那个小小的红色文件夹\NI watched that little red folder right there...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.09,1:08:25.92,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,四次经手...\Ngo through four pairs of hands...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.22,1:08:28.42,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,才到达您手里\Nbefore it got to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.43,1:08:30.43,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,当然这还不包括\N'Course that doesn't include...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.43,1:08:33.81,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,文件送到十九楼之前\Nthe 22 or so other Ford employees
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.81,1:08:34.94,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,很可能会接触文件的\Nwho probably poked at it
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.94,1:08:36.84,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,二十多位其他福特员工\Nbefore it made its way up to the 19th floor.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:38.91,1:08:40.10,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,恕我直言  先生\NAll due respect, sir,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.40,1:08:43.10,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,官僚主义是无法赢下比赛的\Nyou can't win a race by committee.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:45.07,1:08:46.52,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,您需要一个负责人\NYou need one man in charge.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.37,1:08:49.65,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,依我之见  好消息是\NNow, the good news, as I see it,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:50.00,1:08:51.82,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,即使面临这些重重困难\Nis that even with all the extra weight...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.08,1:08:56.08,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我们还是成功摆布了\Nwe still managed to put old Mr. Ferrari
Dialogue: 0,1:08:56.08,1:08:57.45,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,法拉利老头\Nexactly where we want him.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:58.84,1:08:59.66,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,是吗\NDid we?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.46,1:09:01.37,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,是的\NOh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.51,1:09:04.62,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,解释一下\NExpand.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.18,1:09:06.92,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这...\NWell...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:09.01,1:09:10.00,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,当然了  我们之前没有...\Nsure, we hadn't...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:11.14,1:09:13.25,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我们还没解决该如何过弯\NWe haven't worked out how to corner yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.44,1:09:15.63,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,发动机过热\NOr stay cool.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.23,1:09:18.68,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,抓地力也不足\NOr stay on the ground.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.02,1:09:20.60,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,而且很多零件都坏了\NAnd a lot of stuff broke.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.53,1:09:24.18,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,事实上  唯一没坏的地方是刹车\NIn fact, the only thing that didn't break was the brakes.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.95,1:09:26.70,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,而且说白了  我们都没办法打包票\NHell, right now, we don't even know
Dialogue: 0,1:09:26.70,1:09:29.31,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,车漆能不能撑24小时不掉色\Nif our paint job will last the whole 24 hours.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:35.50,1:09:36.86,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,但最后一圈\NBut our last lap...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:37.46,1:09:41.12,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我们在慕尚直道上跑出了350公里的时速\Nwe clocked 218 miles an hour down the Mulsanne Straight.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:41.71,1:09:45.00,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,虽然恩佐老头有多年赛车经历\NNow, in all his years of racing...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:45.88,1:09:49.42,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他也没见过能跑这么快的车\Nold Enzo ain't never seen anything move that fast.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:50.56,1:09:51.79,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,现在他明白了\NAnd now he knows...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.52,1:09:53.59,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,毫无疑问\Nwithout a doubt...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:55.44,1:09:57.09,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我们的车要比他的快\Nwe're faster than he is...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.82,1:10:02.35,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,哪怕是我们派错了车手上场\Neven with the wrong driver...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:03.74,1:10:04.89,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,还存在官僚主义\Nand all the committees.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.03,1:10:08.73,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他此时此刻\NAnd that's what he's thinking about
Dialogue: 0,1:10:08.95,1:10:12.65,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,坐在意大利摩德纳想的就是这件事\Nwhile he's sitting in Modena, Italy... right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:14.87,1:10:16.65,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,那家伙现在吓坏了\NThat man is scared to death...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.87,1:10:20.63,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他怕您今年会变得足够明智\Nthat this year you actually might be smart enough
Dialogue: 0,1:10:20.63,1:10:21.87,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,开始信任我\Nto start trusting me.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:25.26,1:10:25.99,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,没错\NSo, yeah...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:28.43,1:10:30.96,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,您完全摆布了法拉利\NI'd say you got Ferrari exactly where you want him.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.98,1:10:35.75,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,不用谢\NYou're welcome.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.95,1:10:54.61,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,过来\NCome here.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:02.96,1:11:05.08,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,看到那座小建筑了吗\NSee that little building down there?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:05.55,1:11:06.83,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,二战期间\NIn World War II...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:07.34,1:11:11.29,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,五分之三的美国轰炸机在那里生产\Nthree out of five US bombers rolled off that line.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:13.72,1:11:15.79,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你以为打败希特勒的是罗斯福吗\NYou think Roosevelt beat Hitler?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:17.43,1:11:18.34,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,再好好想想\NThink again.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:18.56,1:11:19.88,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这不是福特汽车公司\NThis isn't the first time
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.90,1:11:22.26,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,第一次上欧洲战场了\NFord Motor's gone to war in Europe.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:24.32,1:11:26.51,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我们会做的可不只是摆弄文件\NWe know how to do more than push paper.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:29.28,1:11:31.81,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这家公司只有一个老大\NAnd there is one man running this company.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:34.20,1:11:35.44,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你直接向他汇报\NYou report to him.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:37.08,1:11:38.02,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,明白了吗\NYou understand me?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:39.00,1:11:39.78,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,是  先生\NYes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.37,1:11:43.91,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,去吧  卡罗尔  准备作战\NGo ahead, Carroll. Go to war.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:47.05,1:11:47.83,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,谢谢您  先生\NThank you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.19,1:12:22.52,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你说得没错\NYou were right.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:22.61,1:12:24.16,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,就是变速箱的问题\NIt's the gearbox.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:24.61,1:12:26.21,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我们开得太心急了\NWe ran too hot.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:27.05,1:12:29.11,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,四个里面坏了三个\NThree out of four of 'em broke.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:29.30,1:12:31.11,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,拉杆也弄坏了另一个\NThe rod blew on the other one.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:35.85,1:12:37.50,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我们要重回赛场了  肯\NWe're going back, Ken.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.35,1:12:44.82,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他们说这次归我全权负责\NThey told me I had "Carte blanche" this time.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:46.22,1:12:49.02,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我查了下  这是法语"胡说八道"的意思\NI looked it up. It's French for "Horseshit."
Dialogue: 0,1:12:49.19,1:12:51.24,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我知道他们肯定还会想尽一切办法\NI know they're gonna squeeze our nuts any way they can
Dialogue: 0,1:12:51.24,1:12:52.84,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,来打压我们\Nsoon as they work out how.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:53.44,1:12:55.10,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,那个...\NWell, the, uh...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:55.86,1:12:57.48,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我买的冰淇淋要化了\Nice cream's melting.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:59.96,1:13:02.05,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,好吧  肯\NAll right. Hey, Ken.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:03.13,1:13:04.90,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你是想让我道歉吗\NYou want me to apologize?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:08.10,1:13:09.51,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,要我求你吗\NYou want me to beg?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:09.51,1:13:11.37,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我也不知道  可以试试\NI don't know. Let's try it out.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:11.38,1:13:13.72,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你先试了再说\NLet's, uh, see how that feels.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:19.74,1:13:21.25,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,肯  对不起\NKen, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:22.35,1:13:23.70,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,真心的\NSincerely.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:27.76,1:13:30.25,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你知道我为了能让赛车上跑道\NDo you have any idea the kind of shit that I had to eat
Dialogue: 0,1:13:30.26,1:13:32.23,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,受了多少脸色吗\Njust to get four wheels on that grid?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:32.23,1:13:32.82,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你不知道\NNo, you don't.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:32.83,1:13:34.92,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,因为你完全不用为那些事操心\N'Cause you don't deal with any of that stuff.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:34.95,1:13:36.99,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,所以别磨叽了  肯  我们还有正事要做\NNow knock it off, Ken. We got work to do,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:36.99,1:13:38.93,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,车又不是从天上掉下来的\Nand this car ain't gonna build itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:47.57,1:13:49.40,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,好  行吧\NOkay. All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:59.63,1:14:00.90,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,天啊\NGod.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:02.48,1:14:03.77,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,给我过来\NCome here.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:04.32,1:14:07.25,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-你他妈就一卖车的  -妈的\N- Bloody car salesman. - Shit!
Dialogue: 0,1:14:09.82,1:14:11.66,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,来啊  吃我一记\NCome on. Now you're gonna get it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:16.18,1:14:17.73,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,松手\NGet off me!
Dialogue: 0,1:14:19.93,1:14:22.06,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,固执的王八蛋\NStubborn son of a bitch.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:23.26,1:14:24.68,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,天啊\NGod!
Dialogue: 0,1:14:27.20,1:14:28.94,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-看好了  -来啊\N- You just look... - Right.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.24,1:14:31.02,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-怎么样  -你...\N- Yeah, now. - You...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.59,1:14:32.39,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你还好吗\NYou all right?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:32.39,1:14:33.74,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,妈的\NShit!
Dialogue: 0,1:14:35.35,1:14:37.10,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,看我不收拾你\NNow you're gonna get it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:38.16,1:14:39.51,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,给我过来\NCome here.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:43.29,1:14:44.65,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,完事\NDone.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:49.04,1:14:50.62,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,莫莉  亲爱的\NMollie, darling.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:51.01,1:14:52.47,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,怎么了  老公\NYes, love?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:52.47,1:14:54.41,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,能给我拿瓶汽水吗\NCan I get a fizzy pop, please?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:55.36,1:14:56.83,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,好的\NYes, love.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:58.22,1:14:59.96,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你要吗  谢尔比\NYou want one, too, Shelby?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:59.96,1:15:02.04,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-别给他  -好  谢了莫莉\N- No. No. - Uh, yes, please, Mollie.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:02.04,1:15:04.30,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,别给他  他自己买去\NNo. He can get his own.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:04.45,1:15:06.15,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,只给我拿就行了\NJust for me, please.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:12.57,1:15:14.08,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,上次干架是什么时候来着\NHow long has that been?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:14.92,1:15:16.97,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,至少得有三四年了\NOh, it's gotta be three or four years, at least.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:16.97,1:15:19.20,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,对  在加州河滨市\NRight. Riverside.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.20,1:15:22.29,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,嗯  美国赛车俱乐部区域锦标赛\NYeah. SCCA Divisional Championship.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.55,1:15:24.24,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你把我手指弄断了\NYou broke my finger.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:24.39,1:15:29.98,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你抓着我手臂\NWhat's that nippy bloody thing
Dialogue: 0,1:15:30.10,1:15:31.67,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,扯奶头那一招是什么来头\Nyou do under the arm, that thing?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.68,1:15:33.50,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我叫那招"羊驼咬奶"\NYeah. I call that the Llama Bite.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:33.50,1:15:34.92,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你还取了个名字\NYou name it?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:35.16,1:15:38.71,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你从哪学来的  女童子军吗\NWhere'd you learn that? The Girl Scouts?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:38.71,1:15:41.24,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-怎么  你想再试一次吗  -给你\N- What? You wanna go again? - Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:42.22,1:15:43.27,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你真好\NYou're an angel.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:43.27,1:15:44.35,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,谢谢\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:44.35,1:15:45.81,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,不客气\NMy pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:46.57,1:15:49.10,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,好了  我准备去趟杂货店\NRight. Well, I'm about to go to the grocery store.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:49.10,1:15:50.83,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,要给你们带什么东西吗\NAnything you think you'll need?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:51.49,1:15:53.60,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,冰淇淋\NUm, ice cream.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:54.52,1:15:56.52,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,冰淇淋就不错  还要...\NIce cream would be good and, uh...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:57.68,1:15:58.98,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,面包\Nbread.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:59.54,1:16:00.55,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,好\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:00.56,1:16:02.34,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我不用  谢谢\NNo, I'm good. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:03.13,1:16:04.52,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,谢谢  莫\NThanks, Moll.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:05.32,1:16:07.38,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你还吃这药治心脏病呢\NYou still take those for your ticker?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:07.44,1:16:09.38,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我是因为好吃才吃的\NOnly 'cause they're so delicious.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:10.38,1:16:12.47,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-去你的  -滚吧\N- Up yours. - Oh, go to hell.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:20.34,1:16:23.07,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,跑起来  加把劲  加把劲\NCome on. Giddy-up. Giddy-up. Giddy-up.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:38.32,1:16:41.19,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,菲尔  这是你的  哥们\NPhil! Here's the one for you, mate.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:41.19,1:16:42.71,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,迪诺  过来\NDino, come here.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:00.77,1:17:01.47,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,怎么样\NWell?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:01.47,1:17:03.68,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,踩油门还是会有滞后感\NThere's still lag when I hit the gas.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:03.68,1:17:05.21,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,把真空次级化油器换了吧\NLet's get rid of the vacuum secondaries.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.22,1:17:06.64,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,查理  拿霍利化油器来\NCharlie, get a Holley carb.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:06.64,1:17:08.69,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我们要重新装配油门总成\NWe're gonna rebuild the throttle assembly.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:08.70,1:17:10.07,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,离迪通拿耐力赛只剩三周时间了\NThree weeks to Daytona,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:10.07,1:17:13.31,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这车还是问题百出\Nand it still feels like a bag of squirrels.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.31,1:17:14.71,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,刹车过热\NBrake heat.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:14.88,1:17:16.40,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,那完全又是另一码事了\NThat's a whole different ball game.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:16.64,1:17:19.07,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,好了  彼得  来跟我溜一圈\NAll right, Petey, let's go for that ride.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:27.60,1:17:29.03,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你在干什么\NWhat are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:30.43,1:17:32.02,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,看到那条缝了吗\NYou see that crack?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:32.02,1:17:33.96,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,那是我过八号弯的记号\NThat's my marker for turn eight.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:36.64,1:17:38.24,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,做什么的  提醒你减速吗\NWhat, to slow down?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:39.66,1:17:42.28,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,轻踩刹车  换低档\NBrush the brakes and downshift.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:44.15,1:17:46.77,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,但你到时候会跑到时速240多公里\NBut you'll be going 150 miles an hour.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:47.36,1:17:48.63,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,没错\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:48.70,1:17:50.33,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,那你怎么看得见呢\NSo how do you see it?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:50.56,1:17:53.67,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,速度是很快  但车在加速的时候\NYou're going fast, but as the car speeds up...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:53.93,1:17:56.24,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,周围的一切都会随之变慢\Neverything else slows down.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:56.24,1:17:58.21,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,不能这么看\NYou don't do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:58.88,1:18:00.88,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,视线要开阔点  对吗\NYou do this. Right?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:00.88,1:18:02.85,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这样你就能看到一切\NAnd then you see everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:05.40,1:18:07.21,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你还留了别的记号吗\NDo you set other markers?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.31,1:18:09.83,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,那是当然\NIndeed I do.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:11.17,1:18:12.48,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,还留了很多\NLots of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.46,1:18:16.52,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,知道了  因为我们不能\NYeah, 'cause you can't just
Dialogue: 0,1:18:16.53,1:18:18.83,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,全程都把赛车逼得太紧  对吗\Npush the car hard the whole way, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:18.83,1:18:21.65,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,没错  你得善待赛车\NThat's right. You have to be kind to the car.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:21.65,1:18:26.10,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你会感觉到这个小可怜在你身下呻吟\NYou feel the poor thing groaning underneath you.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:26.71,1:18:30.69,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,如果你想将一台机器推向极致\NIf you're gonna push a piece of machinery to the limit
Dialogue: 0,1:18:30.75,1:18:32.52,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,还指望着它不会散架\Nand expect it to hold together,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:32.52,1:18:36.78,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,那你就得感觉到它的极限在哪里\Nyou have to have some sense of where that limit is.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:39.96,1:18:41.48,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,看前方\NLook out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:41.74,1:18:44.99,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,那就是完美的一圈\NOut there is the perfect lap.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:47.00,1:18:48.69,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,毫无差错\NNo mistakes.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.05,1:18:51.86,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,每次换档  每次过弯\NEvery gear change, every corner...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:52.97,1:18:54.34,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,都恰到好处\Nperfect.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:55.68,1:18:57.08,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你看到了吗\NYou see it?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:01.09,1:19:02.64,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,应该看到了\NI think so.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:04.28,1:19:05.94,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,很多人都看不到\NMost people can't.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:07.18,1:19:10.19,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,很多人甚至都不知道它的存在  但它就在那\NMost people don't even know it's out there, but it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:12.26,1:19:13.60,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,就在眼前\NIt's there.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:16.48,1:19:18.01,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你想吃冰淇淋吗\NYou want some ice cream?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.44,1:19:22.23,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-好啊  -行\N- Yeah. - All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:22.86,1:19:24.20,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我们走\NCome on, then.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:24.49,1:19:26.05,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你知道这是什么记号吗\NDo you know what this marker is?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:26.05,1:19:27.14,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-什么  -那个\N- What? - That one.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:27.14,1:19:29.06,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,扯我手指  你就知道了\NPull my finger. You'll find out.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:50.95,1:19:52.89,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他还要多久才进站\NHow much longer before he comes in?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:53.08,1:19:55.59,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我们每四个小时换一次车手\NUh, well, we change drivers every four hours,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:55.59,1:19:57.53,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-大概还要十分钟  -不  等等\N- so about 10 minutes. - No, hang on.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:57.53,1:19:59.96,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你的意思是现在由毕比全权负责了\NYou're saying Beebe is 100 percent in charge now?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:59.96,1:20:02.25,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,没错  他想让迈尔斯走人\NYes, and he wants Miles gone.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:02.41,1:20:04.54,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,听着  他摆明了是在针对他\NLook, it's personal with this guy.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:04.70,1:20:06.83,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,而且他确实有和你对着干的资本\NAnd, yes, he has the leverage to stick it to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:06.83,1:20:08.64,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他和大魔王明天就坐飞机过去\NHe and the Deuce are flying there tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:08.64,1:20:09.78,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他到时候会当面告诉你\NHe's gonna tell you in person.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:09.78,1:20:11.94,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他现在就等着你失控发飙了\NNow, all he is hoping for is that you lose your cool.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:12.88,1:20:14.37,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,是时候妥协了\NIt's time to let this go.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:14.37,1:20:15.80,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你不能葬送全局\NYou cannot destroy the whole thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:15.80,1:20:17.14,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,不能为了这区区一个人\NNot for one goddamn guy.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:17.15,1:20:19.00,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-我当然可以  -有什么必要呢\N- Sure, I can. - Well, why?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:19.00,1:20:20.27,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,因为在我们说话这会\N'Cause while we're here talking,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:20.27,1:20:22.06,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他正在外头做实事\Nhe's out there getting it done.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:30.46,1:20:31.92,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,糟了\NOh, shit!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:32.91,1:20:34.51,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他刹车失灵了\NHe's got brake fade.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:41.79,1:20:43.26,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,慢点\NEase off!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:53.14,1:20:54.36,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,卡罗尔\NCarroll?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:54.36,1:20:55.76,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-快救他出来  -彼得\N- Get him out! - Peter!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:55.76,1:20:57.37,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,别站这  快进去\NGo on. Go inside.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:57.60,1:20:58.55,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,待在这里别动\NJust stay there.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:58.55,1:21:00.01,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-快救肯  -肯\N- Get Ken! - Ken!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:00.02,1:21:01.50,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,快救他出来\NGet him out!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:03.17,1:21:04.24,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他在这里\NThere he is!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:04.24,1:21:05.65,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,肯\NKen!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:11.76,1:21:12.92,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我看到他了\NI can see him.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:12.92,1:21:14.68,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-肯  -快点\N- Ken! - Come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:21.07,1:21:22.54,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,刹车\NThe brakes.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:31.86,1:21:34.72,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,把这破发动机拆了行吗\NLet's just rip out the damn engine. All right?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:34.72,1:21:37.40,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,无法制动的话要它有什么用\NWe can't use it if we can't stop.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:37.40,1:21:39.14,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我们要是悠着点开\NYou know, the brakes would last longer
Dialogue: 0,1:21:39.14,1:21:40.83,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,刹车还是能撑一会的\Nif we slowed down a bit.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:40.84,1:21:43.47,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,那不就违背要给车加动力的初衷了吗\NWouldn't that defeat the whole purpose of the extra power?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:44.25,1:21:45.32,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我还以为我们在这里这么努力\NYou know, I thought the whole point
Dialogue: 0,1:21:45.32,1:21:47.06,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,是为了拿下比赛呢\Nwas to win the damned race.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:47.41,1:21:49.63,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,要不我们重新设计总成\NMaybe we could design a new assembly.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:49.63,1:21:53.61,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我们在进站时不要仅仅更换刹车片\NInstead of swapping out the pads in the pits...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:53.71,1:21:56.28,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,而是换掉整个刹车系统\Nswap out the entire braking system.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:56.32,1:21:57.92,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,包括刹车盘\NRotors included.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:58.63,1:22:00.00,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,换上一个新的\NPut in a fresh one.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:00.00,1:22:01.70,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,等等  等等  老爹\NWait, wait, wait, Pops,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:01.81,1:22:03.13,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我们能那么做吗\Nare we allowed to do that?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:03.13,1:22:06.02,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,不知道  我看不懂法语\NI don't know. I don't read French.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:05.86,1:22:08.84,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,勒芒24小时耐力赛\N赛车场指南
Dialogue: 0,1:22:07.81,1:22:12.49,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,刹车也是"一种零件"  对吧\NWell, brakes are "a part" like any other, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:12.49,1:22:15.09,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我们可以换零件\NWe are allowed to change parts.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:15.09,1:22:17.03,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,没错  但有时间换吗\NYes. Will we have time to do that?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:17.04,1:22:18.82,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我还不知道  查理\NI don't know yet, Charlie.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.32,1:22:20.95,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我要带他回家了\NI'm gonna take him home.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:21.00,1:22:22.29,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,好\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:22.30,1:22:23.45,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,解决这破事\NSort this shit out.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:23.45,1:22:24.77,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我会的\NI will.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:34.07,1:22:36.43,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你身上着过火吗\NHave you ever been on fire?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:39.33,1:22:42.39,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,没有  我没遇到过这种情况\NWell, no, it's never happened to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:44.55,1:22:49.34,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,不过赛车服是防火的  知道吗\NBut the suit's flameproof, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:49.34,1:22:51.50,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,它能隔热\NIt keeps heat out.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:52.64,1:22:54.04,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,好吧\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:54.96,1:22:58.98,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,但路易斯-埃文斯在摩洛哥大奖赛中被烧死\NBut Lewis-Evans burned to death in the Moroccan Grand Prix.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:58.98,1:23:01.09,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他也穿了防火赛车服\NHe had a flameproof suit on.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.40,1:23:04.92,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,没错  但是...\NYeah, but...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:07.84,1:23:09.55,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他被卡住了\NSee, he got stuck.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:09.55,1:23:11.11,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,无法呼吸\NHe couldn't breathe.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:12.09,1:23:15.71,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,只要人下了车  就没事\NSo, as long as you get out of the car, you're okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:19.41,1:23:21.00,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,爸爸下了车\NDad got out.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:22.33,1:23:24.61,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-确实  -彼得\N- He sure did. - Peter!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:28.38,1:23:29.70,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,再见\NBye.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:30.02,1:23:31.31,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,再见\NSee ya.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.01,1:23:35.75,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-你没事吧  -没事\N- You all right? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:36.76,1:23:38.19,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你怎么回事\NWhat's wrong with you?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:38.97,1:23:40.38,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,别跟我说刹车\NAnd don't be telling me brakes
Dialogue: 0,1:23:40.38,1:23:42.80,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,或者我差点一命呜呼什么的\Nor me almost kicking the bucket out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:42.80,1:23:45.32,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,跟那些穿西装的人有关  对吧\NIt's something to do with the suits, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.45,1:23:49.06,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,都在控制之中\NIt's under control.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:49.08,1:23:50.47,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,怎么了\NWhat is it?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:50.51,1:23:52.30,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我们说过你做好你的事\NYou know how we talked about how you do your thing,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:52.30,1:23:53.34,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我做好我的事\NI do my thing?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:53.34,1:23:54.61,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-这是我的事  -说真的  谢尔...\N- This is my thing. - Really, Shel...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:54.62,1:23:56.39,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,相信我  肯\NJust trust me, Ken.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:56.88,1:23:58.37,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你有计划吗\NYou got a plan?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:59.06,1:24:00.51,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,必须的\NAbsolutely.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:00.81,1:24:02.23,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,好计划吗\NIt a good one?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:02.67,1:24:04.15,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,风险很高\NIt's high risk.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:04.31,1:24:05.48,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,有多高\NHow high risk?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:05.48,1:24:07.18,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,极其高\NExtremely high risk.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:08.65,1:24:10.33,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,了不起\NWell, that's something.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:10.83,1:24:12.89,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-很高兴我们谈了  -随时再聊\N- Glad we had this talk. - Anytime.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:25.21,1:24:27.65,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,福特先生  真是惊喜\NMr. Ford, this is a surprise.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:28.38,1:24:30.99,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,抱歉擅自前来  谢尔比先生\NApologies for the unannounced intrusion, Mr. Shelby,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:30.99,1:24:34.25,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,但是我付了九百万造汽车\Nbut when a man pays $9 million for an automobile,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:34.26,1:24:36.11,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,起码应该能看看长什么样\Nhe ought to at least be able to see it.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:36.11,1:24:37.78,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,听起来很合理\NWell, that sounds reasonable enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:37.79,1:24:39.61,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,谢尔比  能和你谈一下吗\NShelby, could I have a word?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.71,1:24:41.00,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,当然\NSure.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:41.05,1:24:42.86,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-私下谈吗  -是的\N- In private? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:42.86,1:24:44.50,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,那样更好\NThat would be preferable.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:44.51,1:24:45.72,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,好吧  菲尔\NAll right. Hey, Phil.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:45.72,1:24:47.53,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你能招呼一下福特先生吗\NYou wanna take care of Mr. Ford here?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:47.53,1:24:49.41,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,福特先生  他是菲尔·雷明顿\NMr. Ford, that's Phil Remington.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:49.50,1:24:50.20,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,当然\NOf course.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:50.21,1:24:51.40,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,来我办公室  里奥\NCome up to my office, Leo.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:51.41,1:24:52.72,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-幸会  先生  -菲尔\N- Pleasure to meet you, sir. - Phil.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:52.73,1:24:54.82,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我带您参观一下您的车\NGive you a little tour of your car.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:55.68,1:24:58.81,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我们拿掉了289小发动机\NWe took out your 289 small block...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:59.48,1:25:02.15,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,换上了7L的427发动机\Nand put in a 427 7-liter.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.47,1:25:07.06,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,首先  我想消除误会\NFirstly, I want to just clear the air.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:07.09,1:25:09.74,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,希望我们之间的分歧\NI hope that whatever disagreements between us
Dialogue: 0,1:25:09.74,1:25:10.95,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,能归结于...\Ncan just be chalked up to...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:11.70,1:25:14.54,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,激烈争论时自然而然的血气方刚\Nnatural red-bloodedness in the heat of battle.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:14.55,1:25:17.51,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,感谢你这么说  里奥  真的\NI appreciate that, Leo. Truly, I do.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:18.70,1:25:22.11,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,谢尔比  我有责任通知你\NIt falls on me, Shelby, to inform you that
Dialogue: 0,1:25:22.11,1:25:26.46,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我被任命为赛车项目的执行总监\NI have been appointed overall executive director of the racing program.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.88,1:25:31.82,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我真心希望这不会成为我们之间的问题\NNow, I do hope that this won't be a problem between us.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:32.41,1:25:34.61,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,里奥  我向你保证  不会的\NWell, I assure you, Leo, it will not.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.95,1:25:46.30,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,卡罗尔\NCarroll...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:46.80,1:25:47.39,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,卡罗尔\NCarroll!
Dialogue: 0,1:25:47.39,1:25:50.01,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,427发动机的最高速是多少\NAnd what is that top speed with the 427?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:50.02,1:25:51.85,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,不如我们开一圈\NWell, why don't we take it for a spin?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.00,1:25:53.63,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-什么  -来吧  福特先生\N- What? - Yeah, go on, Mr. Ford.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:53.63,1:25:56.47,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-上车  来吧  -你想让我...\N- Hop on in. Go on. - You want me to...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:56.47,1:25:58.86,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,感觉一下九百万的车是什么样\NJust see what $9 million feels like.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.73,1:26:01.98,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,老天\NGod...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:05.73,1:26:07.07,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,把门打开\NOpen the door!
Dialogue: 0,1:26:07.07,1:26:08.67,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,把门打开\NOpen the door!
Dialogue: 0,1:26:08.96,1:26:10.68,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,把门打开\NOpen the door!
Dialogue: 0,1:26:13.34,1:26:14.39,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你扶着我这里\NJust hold me right there,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:14.39,1:26:15.79,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你抓住我的手\Nand you take my hand.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:17.70,1:26:20.44,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,天啊  我坐到了蛋蛋\NOh, God. I sat on my nuts.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:20.44,1:26:23.03,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,下一辆车我们会改进舒适感  别担心\NWe're gonna build the next one for comfort. Don't you worry.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:32.33,1:26:34.12,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-打开门  -抱歉  先生  稍等一下\N- Open the door. - Sorry, sir, if you just give me a moment.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:34.12,1:26:35.60,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-打开门  -这门不好开\N- Open the door. - It's a sticky one.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:36.49,1:26:37.36,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,准备好了吗\NYou ready?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:37.36,1:26:39.20,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,方向盘中间那名字应该能让你知道\NThe name on the middle of that steering wheel should tell you
Dialogue: 0,1:26:39.20,1:26:41.51,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我生来就准备好了  谢尔比  出发\Nthat I was born ready, Shelby. Hit it.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:41.51,1:26:42.24,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,好样的\NAttaboy.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.62,1:26:48.56,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这车推背感挺强  是吧\NIt's got a little kick, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:48.84,1:26:51.07,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-打开门  -好了\N- Open this door. - There we go.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:51.07,1:26:53.22,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,天呐  毕比先生  你还好吗\NGood God, Mr. Beebe. You okay, sir?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:55.34,1:26:57.15,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,天啊\NOh, my God!
Dialogue: 0,1:26:58.99,1:27:01.57,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,天啊  天啊\NOh, my God! Oh, my God!
Dialogue: 0,1:27:04.71,1:27:06.60,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,棒极了\NYeah, baby.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:06.60,1:27:08.18,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,棒极了\NYeah, baby.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:12.20,1:27:16.60,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,差不多就是这会外行会吓得尿裤子\NIt's about right now the uninitiated have a tendency to soil themselves.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:23.68,1:27:25.45,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,天啊\NOh, my God!
Dialogue: 0,1:28:02.58,1:28:04.03,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,福特先生\NMr. Ford...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:07.68,1:28:09.07,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,您没事吧\NYou okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:12.51,1:28:13.86,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,福特先生\NMr. Ford...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:14.32,1:28:15.37,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,您还好吗\Nyou all right?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.37,1:28:17.07,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,真没想到\NI had no idea.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:19.40,1:28:21.17,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,真没想到\NI had no idea.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:23.79,1:28:25.45,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我真希望我爸爸\NI wish my daddy...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:25.56,1:28:27.64,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,能活着看到这个\Nhe were alive to see this.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:29.04,1:28:30.67,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,感受这个\NTo feel this.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:32.06,1:28:35.37,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这不是一台随便谁都能进来轻松掌控的车\NNow, this is not a machine just anybody can get in and easily control.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:35.37,1:28:37.03,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,绝对不是\NAbsolutely not.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:37.37,1:28:38.57,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,真没想到\NI had no idea.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:38.57,1:28:40.29,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,您想赢得勒芒赛\NNow, you wanna win Le Mans.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:40.85,1:28:42.28,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,如果您真的想赢得第一名\NIf you really wanna take first place,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:42.28,1:28:44.19,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,肯·迈尔斯就是你的人选\NKen Miles is the man to do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:53.01,1:28:54.50,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,来得真巧\NGood timing.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:54.56,1:28:57.34,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他了解这车  因为是他帮我造的\NNow, he knows this car because he helped me build it.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:58.59,1:29:02.34,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,谢尔比  你知道我已经任命里奥·毕比\NShelby, you know I've already appointed Leo Beebe
Dialogue: 0,1:29:02.34,1:29:05.20,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-为赛车总监  -正因如此我才和您谈\N- director of racing. - Which is exactly why I'm talking to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:06.01,1:29:08.98,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,您让肯·迈尔斯在迪通拿耐力赛上场\NNow, you let Ken Miles race Daytona.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:09.38,1:29:10.95,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,如果他赢了\NIf he wins...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:11.71,1:29:13.38,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他就在勒芒赛上场\Nhe gets to drive Le Mans.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:15.93,1:29:17.62,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,如果他没赢呢\NAnd if he doesn't?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:18.17,1:29:21.84,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,福特汽车公司获得谢尔比美国公司的全部所有权\NFord Motor Company gets full ownership of Shelby American.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:21.84,1:29:23.25,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,完全控制权  股份以及品牌\NLock, stock, and brand.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:23.25,1:29:24.66,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,永远\NForever.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:27.79,1:29:30.74,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,迪通拿24小时耐力赛进行到第六个小时\NWe're in hour six at the Daytona 24,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.74,1:29:33.20,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,福特车称霸排行榜\Nand Fords are dominating the leaderboard.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:34.21,1:29:36.96,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,谢尔比美国车队的肯·迈尔斯稍微领先\NShelby American's Ken Miles holds a narrow lead
Dialogue: 0,1:29:36.96,1:29:40.57,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,沃尔特·汉斯根驾驶的霍尔曼-穆迪车队的福特\Nover the Holman-Moody Ford driven by Walt Hansgen.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:41.13,1:29:43.21,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我可不那么认为  沃尔特\NI don't bloody think so, Walt.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:02.32,1:30:04.99,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这场比赛不只是对我们车辆的测验\NThis race is not just a test of our cars,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:04.99,1:30:06.51,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,也是对我们团队的测验\Nbut also our teams.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:06.51,1:30:08.53,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你们也知道  我们今天有第二支团队上场\NAs you know, we have a second team out there today.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:08.53,1:30:10.68,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-霍尔曼-穆迪车队  -没错\N- Holman-Moody. - That's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:11.35,1:30:12.59,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,95号  汉斯根\NNumber 95, Hansgen,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:12.59,1:30:14.62,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,飞驰过前部三角环道\Nblisters through the front tri-oval
Dialogue: 0,1:30:14.62,1:30:16.07,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,逼近肯·迈尔斯\Nwhile closing in on Ken Miles.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:16.07,1:30:17.66,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,沃尔特把车开得太快了\NWalt's pushing her too fast.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:17.66,1:30:19.69,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他要开到七千转\NHe's pushing 7,000 RPM.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:19.69,1:30:21.47,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,把提示放慢的牌子放出去\NGet the EZ sign out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:21.47,1:30:23.23,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,快点  动起来  立刻去\NCome on. Move. Do it now.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:23.23,1:30:25.23,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,今天场上的每台GT\NEvery one of these GTs out there today
Dialogue: 0,1:30:25.23,1:30:27.13,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,都受我直接监管\Nis under my direct supervision.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:27.13,1:30:30.26,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,当然还有亨利·福特二世\NAnd of course the supervision of Henry Ford II.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:30.26,1:30:33.53,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,车手  速度  策略\NThe drivers, the speed, the strategy...
Dialogue: 0,1:30:33.60,1:30:37.10,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,甚至转速都由我们决定\Neven the RPMs are determined by us.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:40.31,1:30:42.40,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,肯·迈尔斯和汉斯根\NKen Miles is locked in a pitched battle
Dialogue: 0,1:30:42.41,1:30:45.15,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,在经过大看台时陷入酣战\Nwith Hansgen as they pass the grandstand.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:48.27,1:30:51.61,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,汉斯根进入1号弯时逼近迈尔斯\NHansgen is taking a run at Miles entering turn one.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:52.01,1:30:53.60,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,迈尔斯被挡死了\NMiles is boxed in.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:54.33,1:30:56.84,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,汉斯根成功超车并取得领先\NHansgen slips by and takes the lead
Dialogue: 0,1:30:56.84,1:30:58.64,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,靠近内场连续弯\Napproaching the infield chicane.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.62,1:31:07.97,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,天呐\NCor blimey!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:07.97,1:31:09.30,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你看到了吗\NDid you see that?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:09.30,1:31:11.19,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,警告旗已出\NThe caution flag is out.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:17.33,1:31:19.94,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,还在跑  我们的车还在跑\NStill racing. We are still racing.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:19.95,1:31:21.19,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,快  伙计们  上\NCome on, guys, let's go!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:21.19,1:31:22.10,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,行动  动起来\NLet's go. Move it.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:22.11,1:31:23.46,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他要进站了\NHe's coming in.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:24.18,1:31:26.11,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,快行动  伙计们  快\NLet's go, let's go, guys. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:26.59,1:31:27.73,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,快  把轮胎抬起来\NGo, tires up.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:27.73,1:31:29.44,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,就是这里  行动  动起来\NHere, right here. Let's go. Let's go. Move it.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:29.44,1:31:31.58,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-油枪来了  -破除杆\N- Fuel flying in. - Breaker bar!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:31.58,1:31:33.22,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-可以了  -检查完毕\N- We're good. - It all checked out.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:33.23,1:31:34.89,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-36  38  -快上\N- 36. 38. - Go! Go!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:34.89,1:31:37.34,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,汉斯根追得太紧了\NHansgen is right up our arse.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:37.35,1:31:39.38,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,如果我能比他先开出维修站\NIf I can just get outta the pit ahead of him...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:39.38,1:31:41.80,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,发动机温度有点高  但我觉得可以撑下来\NShe's running hot, but I think she'll hold.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:41.80,1:31:43.36,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-燃油不足  -拿铲子\N- Fuel's low. - Bring up the scoop.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:43.36,1:31:44.83,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,温度有点高\NShe's hot.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:46.75,1:31:48.80,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你好  沃尔特  很高兴见到你\NHey there, Walt. Good to see you.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:48.80,1:31:50.49,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,等我开出这里  谢尔比\NYeah, after I get out of this pit, Shelby,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:50.50,1:31:51.59,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你就高兴不起来了\Nit's the last time you will.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:51.59,1:31:52.96,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,不用担心\NDon't worry.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:52.96,1:31:54.73,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我们有后视镜\NWe got rearview mirrors.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:55.60,1:31:57.55,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,被他逼出赛道的野马怎么样了\NWhat happened to that Mustang he took out?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:57.90,1:31:59.40,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,还不知道\NDon't know yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:59.59,1:32:02.44,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我可以开到六千转以上  谢尔\NI can push her harder than six, Shel.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:02.44,1:32:03.31,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我能感觉到\NI can feel it.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:09.48,1:32:12.28,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,为什么这些人检修加油比我们快这么多\NHow come these guys pit so much faster than we do?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:12.45,1:32:15.89,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,因为他们有纳斯卡车赛团队\NThey got a goddamn NASCAR crew, that's why.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:16.04,1:32:17.96,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-不是吧  -是的\N- No shit? - No shit.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:18.39,1:32:20.13,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,快  快\NGo! Go, come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:21.92,1:32:23.23,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,可以了  可以了\NWe're clear, we're clear.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:23.23,1:32:24.44,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,该死的纳斯卡车赛团队\NGoddamn NASCAR crew.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:24.44,1:32:25.95,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,出发  出发\NGo, go, go!
Dialogue: 0,1:32:26.57,1:32:28.63,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,伙计们  他们已经离开了\NGuys, they've already left.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:30.91,1:32:32.04,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,喂\NHello?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:32.04,1:32:34.20,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我的莫莉  你好\NThere's my Mollie. Hello.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:34.74,1:32:35.90,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你好  亲爱的\NHiya, love.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:35.90,1:32:37.81,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-妈妈  妈妈  -你在做什么\N- Mom? Mom? - What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:38.12,1:32:39.09,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,在喝茶\NJust having a cuppa.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:39.09,1:32:40.87,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,妈妈  问他刹车的情况\NMom, ask him about the brakes.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:40.87,1:32:43.06,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-去睡觉  已经凌晨一点了  -问他\N- Go to bed. It's 1:00 a.M. - Ask him.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:43.06,1:32:44.64,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,去睡觉  马上\NGo to bed. Now.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:44.64,1:32:46.54,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我猜他还没睡\NI take it he's not asleep.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:46.55,1:32:48.27,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他肯定偷偷拿了收音机\NI'm sure he smuggled in a radio.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:48.27,1:32:49.60,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,是啊\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:49.73,1:32:51.42,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他让我问  "刹车怎么样了"\NHe said to ask, "How are the brakes?"
Dialogue: 0,1:32:51.42,1:32:52.98,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,刹车  对  没事\NThe brakes? Yes. No, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:52.98,1:32:55.33,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,告诉他  刹车暂时还能用\NTell him they're working for now.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:55.34,1:32:58.19,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,谢尔比一直表现得很奇怪\NYou know, Shelby's been acting very strange.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:58.32,1:32:59.27,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-福特已经去  -肯\N- Ford have gone... - Ken.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:59.27,1:33:00.67,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,组建了另一支队伍\Nand put up another team.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:00.67,1:33:01.67,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-开一辆GT  -肯\N- With a GT. - Ken.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:01.67,1:33:04.46,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,某种愚蠢的狗屁公司测试之类的\NSome sort of yampy, bloody corporate test or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:04.46,1:33:05.08,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我不知道  但是...\NI don't know, but...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:05.82,1:33:07.44,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,有机会的话就休息一会\NJust take a rest whenever you get a chance.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:07.44,1:33:08.92,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,抱歉  亲爱的  你说什么\NSorry, my love, what were you saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:08.92,1:33:10.35,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你只有几个小时了\NYou've only got a few hours.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:10.35,1:33:11.78,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我听不太清楚\NI can't hear you very well.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:11.79,1:33:13.13,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,抱歉  我听不清\NI'm sorry. I can't hear you.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:13.13,1:33:14.36,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,祝我好运吧\NWish me luck.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:14.37,1:33:16.32,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-祝你好运  -我爱你  亲爱的\N- Good luck. - I love you, darling.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:16.69,1:33:19.05,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,迪通拿耐力赛已经进行了23小时\NAfter 23 hours here at Daytona,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:19.06,1:33:21.61,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,驾驶着绿白色福特的沃尔特·汉斯根\NWalt Hansgen driving the green and white Ford
Dialogue: 0,1:33:21.62,1:33:25.50,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,遥遥领先肯·迈尔斯和谢尔比美国车队\Nhas a commanding lead over Ken Miles and Shelby American
Dialogue: 0,1:33:25.50,1:33:28.45,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,其他选手都已经落下一大截\Nas the rest of the field has fallen off the pace.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:28.45,1:33:29.87,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我们输定了\NWe're locked out.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:29.88,1:33:32.51,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,比赛到这阶段迈尔斯也无能为力了\NAin't nothing Miles can do this late in the race.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:33.07,1:33:35.87,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,发动机过热  我们要把转速压在六千以下\NEngine's hot. We gotta keep it under six thou.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:21.06,1:34:21.92,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,上到七千转\N拼命冲刺
Dialogue: 0,1:34:23.33,1:34:25.14,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,好啊\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:50.23,1:34:51.96,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,车可能会散架的\NShe could come apart.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:51.96,1:34:53.54,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,不试试怎么知道\NOne way to find out.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:56.46,1:34:58.94,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我们不是让他别超过六千转吗\NI thought we were keeping him under 6,000?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:59.21,1:35:00.74,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,闭嘴  唐\NShut up, Don.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:10.48,1:35:12.62,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,迪通拿耐力赛仅剩下最后几分钟\NWith only minutes of racing left here at Daytona,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:12.62,1:35:14.82,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,争夺第一名的决战突然打响\Na pitched battle for the lead is being waged
Dialogue: 0,1:35:14.82,1:35:17.61,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,福特98号在比赛的最后发起惊人的冲刺\Nas the number 98 Ford makes an incredible late surge.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:17.61,1:35:19.74,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-怎么了  -他在加速\N- What's happening? - He's moving up.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:19.74,1:35:21.29,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,进入了前部三角环道\N...entering the front tri-oval,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:21.29,1:35:23.79,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,肯·迈尔斯志在夺冠的最后一搏可能会...\NKen Miles' desperate bid for the win may prove to be...
Dialogue: 0,1:35:32.17,1:35:32.96,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,加油\NCome on now!
Dialogue: 0,1:35:32.96,1:35:35.14,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,白旗  最后一圈\NWhite flag! Last lap!
Dialogue: 0,1:35:40.47,1:35:42.73,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,迈尔斯把他逼得很紧\NMiles is pushing him. Hard.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:53.34,1:35:55.28,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,就是这样  宝贝\NThat's it, girl.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:05.53,1:36:07.39,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,肯·迈尔斯紧跟沃尔特·汉斯根\NKen Miles drafts Walt Hansgen
Dialogue: 0,1:36:07.39,1:36:09.16,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,进入了最后一个弯道\Ncoming into the final turn.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:35.51,1:36:36.78,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,快呀  快呀\NCome on. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:40.32,1:36:41.72,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,搞什么\NWhat the hell?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:49.74,1:36:50.63,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,加油\NCome on.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:51.57,1:36:52.81,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,好了\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:56.99,1:36:58.77,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,好好看着吧\NLook at this now.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:03.58,1:37:04.70,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,妈的\NDamn it!
Dialogue: 0,1:37:13.97,1:37:16.16,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,肯·迈尔斯夺得第一\NKen Miles takes the checkered flag,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:16.16,1:37:18.63,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,为谢尔比美国车队争得荣耀\Nbringing glory to Shelby American.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:21.49,1:37:22.69,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,怎么样啊\NHow about that?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:32.71,1:37:33.89,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,可靠性  强度...\NReliability, strength...
Dialogue: 0,1:37:34.60,1:37:35.56,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,喂  里奥\NYes, Leo.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:35.56,1:37:37.65,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,福特先生  我们赢了\NMr. Ford, sir, we won.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:39.74,1:37:42.05,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我们赢了  福特赢了迪通拿耐力赛\NWe won! Ford won Daytona.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:42.05,1:37:43.26,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,太好了\NHot damn.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:43.84,1:37:45.82,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,哪支队赢了  里奥\NAnd which team was it, Leo?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:46.94,1:37:49.62,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,谢尔比美国车队  车手是迈尔斯\NShelby American. Miles driving.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:51.17,1:37:52.73,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这混蛋\NSon of a bitch.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:53.34,1:37:54.21,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,好了\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:55.07,1:37:56.27,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他到底去哪了\NWhere the hell is he?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:56.41,1:37:58.67,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,等等  我看见他了  等下\NHang on, I see him. Hey, wait.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:58.67,1:38:01.24,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,有人在沙滩上走失一条斗牛犬\NSomeone lost a bulldog on the beach.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:02.35,1:38:04.39,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,别别  快来吧\NNo, no. Come on. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:05.22,1:38:08.43,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,快来  来来来\NCome on. Let's go. Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:08.43,1:38:11.35,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,快把酒给他  把酒给他\NSomeone get this man a drink. Someone get him a drink.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:29.04,1:38:31.57,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,快睡觉  你在做什么呢\NIn bed, you. What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:31.82,1:38:33.62,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,夜猫子\NDirty stop out.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:33.78,1:38:34.86,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我是在...\NI was...
Dialogue: 0,1:38:35.75,1:38:38.77,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,画地图  这样就能知道你在勒芒的赛况\Ndrawing a map, so I could follow you on Le Mans.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:42.89,1:38:44.11,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,看看\NLook at that.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:45.53,1:38:47.23,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,画得完全正确\NThat is spot on.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:47.23,1:38:49.87,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你真是高手  非常准确\NYou are a dab hand, very accurate.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:51.36,1:38:52.90,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,跟我说说赛道吧\NTell me about the track.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:52.90,1:38:54.61,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,不行  彼得\NNo, I can't, Petey.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:55.09,1:38:56.33,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,求你了\NPlease.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:04.54,1:39:06.91,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,从起点线出发\NWell, you start at the start line.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:07.31,1:39:09.29,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,对  但你其实是从这里出发的\NYeah, but you actually start here
Dialogue: 0,1:39:09.29,1:39:11.41,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,因为在勒芒赛你得跑向你的车\Nbecause you have to run to your car at Le Mans.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:11.41,1:39:12.51,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,没错\NTrue enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:12.88,1:39:16.47,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,一旦你老爸成功挪过去\NSo, once your old man manages to hobble over...
Dialogue: 0,1:39:16.77,1:39:19.24,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-把车开出来  -还没撞到别的车\N- and pull out... - And not hit anyone.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:19.24,1:39:20.82,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,对  没错\NYes, right.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:22.09,1:39:26.38,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,然后就要全力加速开往邓洛普桥\NThen you accelerate very hard up to Dunlop Bridge...
Dialogue: 0,1:39:26.57,1:39:28.47,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,路向一边倾斜\Nroad banking away from ya
Dialogue: 0,1:39:28.48,1:39:31.45,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,经过树丛就到了埃索斯连续弯\Nand down through the trees to the Esses...
Dialogue: 0,1:39:31.45,1:39:33.63,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,再加速进入特鲁热加速弯\Nand accelerate up to Tertre Rouge.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:33.63,1:39:36.19,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这是个关键的一档弯\NCritical first gear corner.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:36.40,1:39:37.76,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,快速入弯\NFast entry.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:38.01,1:39:40.91,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,保持高速出弯  进入...\NKeep your speed up for your exit onto...
Dialogue: 0,1:39:41.82,1:39:43.09,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,慕尚直道\NMulsanne.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:43.54,1:39:46.36,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这是一段很长的直路  被白杨簇拥着\NLong straightaway, hemmed in by poplars.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:46.36,1:39:49.92,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,挂最高档  开到时速338公里\NTop gear, 210 miles per hour.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:49.92,1:39:52.16,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,然后退到三档  提高转速\NAnd down to third, revs up.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:52.16,1:39:54.04,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,转速就是你的朋友\NRevs are your friend.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:54.47,1:39:58.02,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,最远距离入弯  让车空档滑行\NGet a maximum exit. Let the car run free.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:58.02,1:40:00.02,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,经过坡顶\NOver the brow...
Dialogue: 0,1:40:00.17,1:40:00.92,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,然后...\Nthen...
Dialogue: 0,1:40:02.89,1:40:04.40,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,经过慕尚弯\NMulsanne Corner.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:04.46,1:40:06.92,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,一路加速到雅致弯\NAccelerate to Arnage
Dialogue: 0,1:40:06.93,1:40:08.46,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,然后爬坡至白屋弯\Nand then over the rise to the White House.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:08.46,1:40:10.99,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,过好这个弯...\NYou get that right and...
Dialogue: 0,1:40:13.77,1:40:16.25,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,24小时比赛里的第一个三分半\Nyour first three and a half minutes...
Dialogue: 0,1:40:16.97,1:40:18.78,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,就过去了\Nof 24 hours.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:19.64,1:40:26.61,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,但是  你没法做到每圈都很完美\NBut... you can't make every lap perfect.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:27.30,1:40:28.84,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,但我可以尽力\NBut I can try.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:34.47,1:40:35.37,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,好了\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:36.86,1:40:38.06,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,快上床睡觉了\NOff to bed, you.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:40.85,1:40:44.09,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我会先来叫醒你\NI will... wake you...
Dialogue: 0,1:40:44.78,1:40:46.63,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,然后再动身去法国\Nbefore I leave for France.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:46.68,1:40:47.83,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我保证\NI promise.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:48.39,1:40:50.77,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,好  晚安\NOkay. Good night.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:19.07,1:41:20.12,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,那个...\NWhere's, um...
Dialogue: 0,1:41:20.82,1:41:23.42,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,圣皮埃尔大酒店怎么走\NWhere's that? The Hotel Saint Pierre?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:24.84,1:41:25.70,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,哪里\NWhere?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:12.51,1:42:14.46,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,明天还会再下雨的\NIt's gonna rain again tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:19.72,1:42:21.46,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这里成天下雨\NThere's always rain here.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:24.65,1:42:26.35,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,但开赛时没有雨\NStart'll be dry though,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:26.35,1:42:29.92,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,所以等下雨了我们再帮你换轮胎\Nso we'll swap out your tires come rain.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:32.27,1:42:33.15,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,好\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:36.68,1:42:40.84,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你还是好好睡一觉比较好  斗牛犬\NMight be smart to sleep, Bulldog.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:42.39,1:42:43.76,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你也一样\NWell, you, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:44.66,1:42:45.97,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,又不是我开车\NI'm not driving.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:48.65,1:42:52.13,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,那还真是可惜了\NThat's a bloody shame, that.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:52.18,1:42:54.39,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我没那技术\NOh, hell, I couldn't make this team.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:59.21,1:43:01.27,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我要走到第一个弯道\NI'm gonna go walk the first corner.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:02.96,1:43:04.24,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我猜到了\NI figured.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:15.35,1:43:16.61,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,就靠这个了\NCounting on it.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:51.52,1:43:52.38,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,肯\NKen.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:52.78,1:43:53.69,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,查兹\NChaz.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:00.26,1:44:01.06,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我们要改一下座椅的颜色\NWe'll change the color of the seats,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:01.06,1:44:02.32,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,对吧  弗罗斯特\Nshall we, Frost?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:08.24,1:44:10.83,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,如果这是选美大赛的话\NWell, if this were a beauty pageant...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:10.96,1:44:12.85,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我们已经输了\Nwe just lost.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:13.74,1:44:15.10,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,看起来跑得挺快  不是吗\NLooks fast, don't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:15.67,1:44:17.32,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,外表可说明不了一切\NLooks aren't everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:21.60,1:44:24.42,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,法拉利是斯卡费奥提和班蒂尼开赛\NScarfiotti and Bandini start for Ferrari.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:30.25,1:44:31.37,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你能赢他\NYou can take him.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:31.37,1:44:33.84,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,四分钟  肯  还有四分钟  伙计\NFour minutes, Ken. Four minutes, buddy.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:33.84,1:44:35.09,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这里是来自法国勒芒的现场直播\NLive from Le Mans, France.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:35.09,1:44:37.18,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,妈  快来\NMom! Come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:37.37,1:44:39.23,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,好了  来了\NAll right, coming.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:39.76,1:44:42.29,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,勒芒24小时耐力赛\NThe 24 Hours of Le Mans.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:42.29,1:44:44.58,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,赛车已经排成一列\NAnd there are the cars lined up...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:46.96,1:44:49.75,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,车手请就位\NDrivers, please take your places.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:08.11,1:45:08.92,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-车手们就在那里  -他在那里\N- And there they are... - There he is.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:08.92,1:45:10.36,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,站成一排  蓄势待发\Nlined up, ready to go.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:09.07,1:45:13.37,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,法国勒芒卫星实况转播
Dialogue: 0,1:45:10.36,1:45:12.08,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他们按照练习赛的用时排位\NThey're lined up as per their practice times.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:12.08,1:45:14.04,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,更快的车排在我们左边\NFaster cars are up to our left.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:04.43,1:46:06.01,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,你他妈在逗我吧\NOh, bloody joking!
Dialogue: 0,1:46:11.70,1:46:14.66,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,比扎瑞尼十号几乎失控\NNumber 10, a Bizzarrini, almost loses control.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:14.95,1:46:16.18,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,没事的\NIt's all right.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:18.97,1:46:20.68,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,您刚刚看起来好极了  先生\NYou looked great out there, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:21.63,1:46:23.28,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,迈尔斯怎么了\NWhat happened to Miles?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:23.89,1:46:25.05,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,邓洛普
Dialogue: 0,1:46:31.70,1:46:33.49,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,天啊\NBloody hell.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:35.57,1:46:36.45,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,不\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:43.37,1:46:45.19,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,狗娘养的\NPoxy bastard.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:20.93,1:47:21.94,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,一圈过后\NAfter one lap,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:21.94,1:47:25.06,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,法拉利的班蒂尼占据首位\NBandini-Ferrari is in first place.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:28.62,1:47:30.36,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,迈尔斯在哪\NWhere is Miles?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:32.40,1:47:33.83,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,肯跑哪去了\NWhere the hell is Ken?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:33.83,1:47:34.90,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我不知道\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:43.71,1:47:44.63,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他要进站了\NHe's coming in.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:45.18,1:47:45.74,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他要进站了\NHe's coming in.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:45.74,1:47:46.97,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,他要进站了  动起来\NHe's going in. Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:46.97,1:47:49.22,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,弗罗斯特  快点  快动起来\NFrosty, come on. Let's go. Move it.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:49.25,1:47:50.88,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,我觉得是车门出了问题\NI think it's his door.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:50.88,1:47:53.64,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,福特车队早早就出师不利\NThat's a rough start for the Ford team so early...
Dialogue: 0,1:47:56.78,1:47:59.76,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这该死的门关不上\NThe bloody door won't close!
Dialogue: 0,1:47:59.76,1:48:02.28,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,没事  没事  我们会解决的\NAll right. All right. We'll take care of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:02.63,1:48:03.72,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,快点  伙计们\NCome on, guys.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:03.72,1:48:04.95,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,这破车门\NDamn door!
Dialogue: 0,1:48:04.97,1:48:05.77,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,-试试  -这样应该就行了\N- Try that. - This'll do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:05.77,1:48:08.16,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,谢尔比  出什么问题了\NShelby, what the hell is wrong?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:08.62,1:48:09.91,外文,NTP,0,0,0,,有东西卡着门框\NSomething's hitting the frame.
